The Oppressed
By: Max Wang


Chapter 1: Nathan, July
        Nathan Francis was a 23-year-old man from Elmwood Village. He was a normal man, with a normal job and a normal life. Nathan had completed high school, graduated from college, and gotten a job at Alpha Market, a local supermarket operated by the renowned Knox Corporation. He chose this job because of the high salary Knox Corporation provided, and how easy it was to work there. In addition, Knox Corporation claimed to be a very sustainable company through the usage of wind turbine power plants, which are tall turbines that convert the kinetic energy of wind into electricity.
Nathan was definitely the right person for the job…he was friendly, hardworking, and optimistic. Slowly, he began climbing the ranks, becoming more and more popular and well-known amongst his colleagues. In one year alone, Nathan had gone from a plain cashier to a store manager. Now, Nathan was getting ready to be promoted to a factory worker and finally get a job at the Knox Corporation headquarters (which was, interestingly, right next to Elmwood Village…). However, in the back of his mind, there was one thing troubling Nathan…the population of his village was dropping fast, almost at the same rate he was climbing the ranks…
Chapter 2: Elmwood Village, July
Elmwood Village was a modest and peaceful community. The residents of the village were cordial and warm, and everyone enjoyed their humble, quiet lives. However, that all changed drastically. While Elmwood Village had an initial population of  12,368 in January, it had unusually dropped to 11, 243 by March. Everyone thought that the sudden drop in population was expected, since the flu was exceptionally strong that year, but this claim would be completely dismissed in May, when the population plummeted to 7,089. Then, in July, the population dropped again, resulting in only 5,321 people remaining. In a matter of a few months, more than half of the people in Elmwood Village had mysteriously passed away. The once  bright, cheerful Elmwood Village had become dreadful and dark. Cries of family and friends could be heard from almost anywhere, nearly every house was draped in black, and swarms of pallbearers marched down every street. Local news reported that such an extreme drop in population had only ever been seen in places that had experienced nuclear disaster. Worst of all, nobody knew how to stop this dreadful crisis.
While everybody was frantically searching for ways to protect their families, Nathan was pondering on how to find a cure. After a while of thought, he concluded two things. Firstly, every poor soul that had passed away died from the same cause: cancer. Secondly, the deaths coincidentally started happening the same month Knox Corporation opened its factory right next to Elmwood Village…


Chapter 3: The Factory, July
Nathan was very excited for his first day as a factory worker. With this new job, he would get almost 50% more money than a store worker. In addition, many others had told him how grand and stunning Knox Corporation’s factory was. However, he was still staggered to see how immense and great the factory actually was with his own eyes. Unable to accept that he would be working in an environment so different from the miniscule Alpha Market, Nathan eagerly rushed inside to see what was in store for him. As he passed through the huge steel gates that encircled the factory, Nathan saw thousands of workers operating on enormous machines that processed the ingredients and turned them into food products. Giant tubes carrying ingredients for the Knox Corporation’s famous food products ran throughout the factory, which passed into places where they would then be processed and packaged. Nathan was assigned to work on one of the ingredient-mixing machines that mixed dough and other elements together. These ingredients would then be baked into bread in another part of the machine. The other workers had told him that their job was quite easy; they just had to supervise the machines and monitor the heat of the baker. Nathan was confused at first, since he had originally thought that his job would be placing food on conveyor belts and dumping ingredients into buckets. However, his colleagues had laughed and told him that the factory was mostly run by machines, and the only humans needed were workers. Nathan’s colleagues had also told him to focus on working instead of asking questions. They said that although there weren’t any managers in the factory, Knox Corporation always seemed to know what they were doing…
By now, Nathan had started to notice a few strange things around the factory. For one, there were lots of security cameras all over the factory. At first, it seemed that the cameras were just for security, but after trying to count every single one he saw (there were just too many), Nathan concluded that the overwhelming number of security cameras were not just there for that. Secondly, all of the machines and tubes were enclosed, so nobody knew what was happening inside of them or what ingredients they were carrying… This made Nathan suspect that Knox Corporation didn’t want their employees and the public to know what ingredients or additives they were putting in their foods. Finally, after counting how many machines there were in the factory, Nathan was certain that the amount of energy required to operate such immense machines and tubes was at least double the amount of energy a wind turbine power plant could produce. After pondering over all of these, Nathan was certain that Knox Corp. was hiding something. However, it didn’t seem to be anything harmful or illegal, so Nathan continued to work hard and tried to stop worrying about these things.


Chapter 4: The Offices, September
        It had happened again. The population of Elmwood Village had once again plummeted, and with that, Nathan had been promoted. During his time at the factory, Nathan had been a great leader. He maintained friendly relationships with everyone, he performed his work diligently, and he had helped with many things like repairing a control station, introducing the factory to new recruits, and even creating a scrumptious new food product. Seeing that he was a natural leader, Knox Corp. had generously decided to promote Nathan to an executive who was allowed to work at the offices.
Nathan, as always, was very excited for his new job. He wondered if he would be as amazed as he was last time about his new workplace. As Nathan boarded the private bus Knox Corp. had sent to take him to the Offices, he noticed that there were security cameras everywhere and that the bus didn’t even have a driver. Instead, it was AI-controlled and Nathan felt very uncomfortable looking around at all the security cameras, so he straightened his posture, tried to act as serious as possible, and quietly waited.
One hour later…
        Nathan stretched his legs as the bus doors automatically opened. It had been a long ride, and trying to maintain a good posture for that long was very exhausting. As he exited the car, Nathan gazed at his surroundings and felt a little bit confused. He had expected the Knox Corporation Offices to be in a large and crowded city. Instead, they were here, in an isolated desert. As Nathan approached the sleek, black doors leading into the offices, two burly security guards, both carrying M16s, stopped him and demanded his ID card. Nathan was very frightened, but then maintained a relaxed composure and pulled out his new ID card Knox Corp. had just given him for inspection. After observing the ID card, the guards almost instantly smiled and welcomed “Mr. Nathan Francis” (as they had called him) into the office. When he entered the office building, Nathan immediately recognized the familiar presence of security cameras everywhere. Indifferent, Nathan walked up a flight of stairs to his room, eager to start working. However, at the top, he was met with a horrifying sight. Hundreds of managers stared down at their computers, closely monitoring everything that was happening through the security cameras. Nathan’s hypothesis was confirmed. He now knew for a fact that every single security camera he had seen was being watched. The lack of privacy made him quite wary, so Nathan hurried down the corridor and into his office. Inside his office, Nathan found a simple desk, an office chair, and a huge monitor. After swiping his ID card to open the computer, Nathan noticed that Knox Corporation had sent him a file labeled the “Executive Loyalty Examination”. After Nathan clicked on it, a series of instructions popped up. It said that Nathan had to complete the test to prove his loyalty to Knox Corporation. It also said that this was required in order for him to start his job as an executive. Although he was puzzled as to why he had to do a test to show his loyalty, Nathan still filled out the test. However, just when he was about to submit, another file popped up on his screen. This time, he knew it wasn’t from Knox Corp. as it was labeled S.O.L.A.R.sAvEm0nths3579.exe. At first, Nathan was unsure of whether to click it or not, wondering if it might be a virus. However, his curiosity ultimately prevailed, and Nathan clicked the file. Instantly, bold and black letters appeared in front of his screen.
KNOX CORPORATION IS NOT WHAT YOU THINK IT IS. IT HAS BEEN DAMAGING ELMWOOD VILLAGE AND HIDING FROM US FOR FAR TOO LONG. YOUR VILLAGE’S EXTREME DROP IN POPULATION IS NOT NATURAL, IT IS LINKED TO YOUR COMPANY. JOIN US TO UNCOVER KNOX CORPORATION’S DARK SECRETS. JOIN US TO FREE YOUR VILLAGE AND SAVE EVERYONE YOU LOVE. JOIN US.  -    S.O.L.A.R.[a][b][c][d]
To be continued…

The Quiet Rebellion
By: Max Wang


Recap: In the Oppressed, we followed the story of Nathan Francis, a 23-year-old man from Elmwood Village. Nathan had originally been a cashier at the local Alpha Market, but since he performed exceptionally well, he quickly got promoted to a factory worker. He would continue to climb up the ranks, becoming an executive who was allowed to work in the Offices. Unfortunately, his villages’ population was dropping just as fast as he was climbing the ranks. In January, there were 12,368 people. Then, the population plummeted, and in July, there were only 5,321 people alive. At the same time, Nathan began to notice a few strange things about the company, Knox Corporation. At first, he did not think that Knox Corp. was linked to the villages’ extreme population decline. This, however, all changed on Nathan’s first day at the Offices after a mysterious file popped up on his screen…
Chapter 4.5: The ending of The Oppressed
This time, he recognized that the file wasn’t from Knox Corp. as it was labeled S.O.L.A.R.sAvEm0nths3579.exe. At first, Nathan was reluctant to click it, wondering if it might be some sort of a virus. However, his curiosity ultimately prevailed, and Nathan clicked on the file. Instantly, bold and black letters appeared in front of his screen.
KNOX CORPORATION IS NOT WHAT YOU THINK IT IS. IT HAS BEEN DAMAGING ELMWOOD VILLAGE AND HIDING FROM US FOR FAR TOO LONG. YOUR VILLAGE’S EXTREME DROP IN POPULATION IS UNNATURAL AND IT IS DIRECTLY LINKED TO YOUR COMPANY. JOIN US TO UNCOVER KNOX CORPORATION’S DARK SECRETS. JOIN US TO FREE YOUR VILLAGE AND SAVE EVERYONE YOU LOVE. JOIN US.
 - S.O.L.A.R.
Chapter 5: Dilemma
        Nathan was dumbfounded. He didn't know what to do. He buried his head into his arms as his heart and mind raced. After quite a while of shock, Nathan began to ponder the message. Now that a mysterious organization had sent him this message linking Knox Corp. to Elmwood Village’s population decrease, Nathan began to connect the dots. He remembered how secretive Knox Corporation was. There were security cameras everywhere, no one could see what was happening inside the food processors, and the Offices were situated in a secluded desert. Not to mention, Knox Corp. had definitely been lying about using wind turbine power plants to supply energy, since it was impossible to produce such an immense amount of power using the kinetic energy of wind. However, Nathan was still troubled by a few important questions: How were these things linked to his villages’ population drop? What evidence was there to prove these claims? What is S.O.L.A.R.? Nathan was trapped in a dilemma. He didn’t know whether to trust Knox Corporation or S.O.L.A.R. Despite this, Nathan was certain about one thing: He had to save his village.
Chapter 6: The Meeting
        That night, Nathan didn’t sleep well. He kept wrestling with who to trust, Knox Corp. or S.O.L.A.R. One was a secretive, suspicious company, while the other was a cryptic and unknown organization. The next day, Nathan came to work weary (he didn’t sleep at all) but excited. On the bus ride, Nathan had thought of an idea that could give him information about both Knox Corp. and S.O.L.A.R. He would send an undisclosed message to S.O.L.A.R. saying that he is indeed skeptical of Knox Corp. However, he would also say that he doesn’t fully trust S.O.L.A.R., and therefore that he required an explanation in order for him to join the organization. After sending this message, Nathan almost immediately got a response:
Hello, Nathan. These are indeed very good questions to ask. However, we cannot reveal these details to you right now, since we cannot fully trust you, and you are being watched. Nevertheless, we will eventually give you the information you need. We will send you a messenger in three days from now at midnight. They will bring you to us, and we will have a crucial meeting.
Three days later…
Nathan stood outside his door, waiting for the messenger to arrive. At 12:00 sharp, a sleek, black car stopped in his driveway. A man wearing black sunglasses stepped out of the car and walked up to Nathan. As he shook Nathan’s hand, he beckoned him towards the car. Reluctantly, Nathan entered the car…
“Hello, Nathan. It is a pleasure to meet you. I’ve heard a lot about you and your actions, and I believe you would really make a great addition to our team.”
“You knew about me already? How?”
The cryptic man chuckled and motioned to the driver. “Why, of course it's because of him!”
The driver turned around and smiled at Nathan. Nathan was so shocked to see who it was, he almost fell off his seat. “Robin!?” He exclaimed.
To Nathan’s disbelief, the driver was Nathan’s best friend, Robin Bernard. The mysterious man explained that his name was Raynell, and that he was the head of S.O.L.A.R. He also told Nathan how he had met Robin, and what they knew about Knox Corporation.
        “Thirteen years ago, I created the Society of Liberation and Rescue, abbreviated as S.O.L.A.R. This organization has been aiding people and animals from around the world. Our organization has saved countless animals from abuse and found cures for unknown diseases. Two years ago, I met your friend, Robin. He is a brilliant man, as you should know, and he found a cure for a deadly disease known as KOVID-29. This year, he told me about your villages’ extreme drop in population. We both know that this is very unusual, and that there must be some cause for this. We began by investigating the cause of the deaths. Since everyone who passed away died of cancer, we started looking for cancer cells. For the first six months, we found nothing, but just a month ago, we found out that the soil, air, and water in your village contains lethal amounts of radioactivity that has caused the residents to develop cancer. We also found out that there were many illegal additives in Alpha Market’s food products. Due to this, we began to secretly investigate your company, Knox Corporation. We concluded two very important points: Firstly, Knox Corporation is very corrupt, and it is putting many illegal additives in its products that can cause cancer. Secondly, the radioactivity in your villages’ soil may suggest that there is nuclear waste, although we don’t know where it came from and why it’s there.”
“So is that what you want me to investigate?”
“Correct. Since you are a high-ranking executive, you have the right to inquire about any company secrets. However, for them to fully let their guard down, you must fill out the Executive Loyalty Examination.”
“But…the final question on the form says that you must swear on your life that you will never betray Knox Corp.”
“Are the consequences actually that harsh and strict?”
“Yes. Knox Corporation has hundreds of thousands of security cameras everywhere, and I think they even have their own SWAT force.”
Raynell pondered for a moment, and then asked Nathan, “We will try to send reinforcements, but this mission will still be very risky, and possibly even life threatening. Would you still like to participate? I would understand if you-”
“Yes. I will participate in this mission, no matter the cost. I must save my village and everyone I hold dear to me.”
“Thank you, Nathan. Thank you for striving to save the people of this society.”
Chapter 7: The Plan
        At S.O.L.A.R. headquarters in Athensvale, Raynell introduced Nathan to everyone else. They all liked Nathan very much and admired him for his bravery. Raynell convened a meeting with everybody else in the organization. He explained that Nathan would continue to work at Knox Corp. undercover and collect as much information on Elmwood Village’s population decline as possible. He also split S.O.L.A.R. into two groups: One would investigate the radioactivity in Elmwood Village, while the other would reinforce Nathan and help relay information. Finally, Raynell gave an stirring speech that moved everyone to tears, restating the purpose of S.O.L.A.R.: Liberation and Rescue, no matter what.
After the meeting, everyone, especially Nathan, was determined to save Elmwood Village. As he headed home, Nathan thought about the challenges he was now about to face. He was now a special man, with a special job and a special life.
To be continued…
The Truth
By: Max Wang


Recap: In the Quiet Rebellion, we followed the story of Nathan Francis, a 23-year-old man from Elmwood Village. After receiving a mysterious message from a cryptic organization called S.O.L.A.R., Nathan grew suspicious of his company, Knox Corp. When he first joined Knox Corp., half a year ago, the population of Elmwood Village began plummeting unnaturally. At first, Nathan didn't think that his village’s extreme drop in population was linked to his company. This is because everyone believed at first that the deaths were caused by the abnormally strong flu. However, after S.O.L.A.R. sent a message to Nathan informing him that his company was linked to the population drop, Nathan connected the dots. He organized a meeting with S.O.L.A.R. 's leader, Raynell, and discovered that his best friend, Robin Bernard, was also a member of S.O.L.A.R. In addition to this, Nathan also found out that his village contained lethal amounts of radiation, and that Knox Corporation’s food products held illegal additives that caused cancer. As a result, Nathan joined S.O.L.A.R., and he was assigned a difficult and extremely important task: Nathan would go undercover as an agent and reveal Knox Corporation’s dark secrets and save his village…


The day after the meeting…


Chapter 8: The Loyalty Examination
        The next day, Nathan came to the Knox Corp. Offices with an anxious expression and a thin, sealed smile. Every time he saw a “security” camera, Nathan would picture himself getting caught and arrested by Knox Corporation’s “security” officers. As Nathan approached the sleek doors leading into the Offices, he saw a bunch of SWAT officers, wearing kevlar vests, and holding shiny, lethal M16s. He imagined his head being pierced by their bullets and felt as scared as a mouse in a snake’s den. Nathan quickly hurried up the stairs and into his office cubicle, since he didn’t want to see any more security cameras or supervisors. After regaining his composure, he opened his computer and started the first step of his mission: The Executive Loyalty Examination. Nathan quickly filled out the form and answered every question without hesitation...until he got to the last question. It said:
Question #44
WILL YOU SWEAR ON YOUR LIFE THAT YOU WILL NEVER BETRAY KNOX CORPORATION?
        Option 1: Yes
        Option 2: ?
        Nathan took a deep breath and once again pictured himself getting arrested and executed. However, this time, he also remembered the pain and agony of his neighbors, who both died of cancer the first month Nathan got hired at Knox Corp. Determined, Nathan checked the yes option and submitted the form. In less than a second, a message from Knox Corp. appeared on Nathan’s computer screen:
Thank you for filling out the form.
REMEMBER–IF YOU BETRAY KNOX CORPORATION, NOTHING SHALL SAVE YOU FROM YOUR FATE.
YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED.
Chapter 9: The Investigation
        After filling out the Executive Loyalty Examination, Nathan was formally allowed to start his work at the Offices. His job was quite simple; he only had to attend Knox Corp. board meetings and contribute to their discussions. However, the most crucial part of Nathan’s job was not this, instead, it was an annual factory check. Every year, all of the executives would gather together at the Knox Corp. factories and for one week straight, they would perform test after test on every single machine and tube in the factory to check if any were broken or in need of maintenance. When Nathan used to be a factory worker, he had experienced the annual factory inspection. He could still clearly recall the day when all of the factory workers were suddenly ushered out of the factory. They were then escorted onto huge black buses that delivered each of them home. When Nathan had inquired about why they had to go off duty so early, one of his colleagues had informed him that it was most likely because of this annual factory check that forced everyone to return home early. Now, after having remembered all of these things about the annual factory inspection, Nathan concluded that the factory check must be very secretive. This is because none of the factory workers were allowed to see it, and the inspection took an entire week. Nathan also realized that since the annual factory check was so secretive, he would definitely be able to uncover some confidential information when he inspected the factory…


Three months later…


        It was finally time for the long awaited factory inspection. During the previous night, Nathan had sent a private message to Raynell. In it, Nathan indicated that he would inform Raynell of any secrets that he would uncover during the week of the factory check. The next day, Nathan boarded the huge buses that Knox Corporation had sent, and after an hour-long drive, he arrived at the Knox Corp. factory. Just like before, Nathan saw that all of the factory workers had been led into buses and taken back to their homes. After there was no one left, Nathan and the other executives exited their buses and entered the factory. Inside, it looked the exact same way it had on the day Nathan got promoted. Humongous food processors were present throughout the factory, and gigantic tubes were hooked up to all of the machines. Nathan suddenly felt a surge of nostalgia and excitement, so he strolled into the immense factory and began inspecting.


        Over the course of the next six days, Nathan and the other executives inspected every single inch of every single machine and tube in the factory. They performed meticulous inspections on each food processor and even checked all of the security cameras in the factory. Unfortunately, Nathan was too busy checking the food processors, and as a result, he didn’t have any time to start investigating. Due to this, he became increasingly bored and discouraged, seeing that the factory inspection would not reveal any of Knox Corporation’s secrets. However, on the night of the sixth day, one of the chief executives told everyone that the seventh day would be the most important, and that there would be hundreds of SWAT officers guarding outside the factory. Alarmed, Nathan quickly sent a private message to S.O.L.A.R. headquarters, telling them that he would uncover the truth on the next day.


The next day…


        After eating breakfast, Nathan and the other executives hurried into the factory at 9:00 sharp. When they arrived, the chief executive was already there. He gave everyone a speech about loyalty and secrecy, and informed them that they would be inspecting confidential things today. Then, the chief executive led Nathan and the other executives to the back of the factory and into a secret door concealed inside the wall…


        It was at this moment that Nathan realized the truth. It was at this moment that Nathan broke through all of Knox Corporation’s lies. It was at this moment that he knew why his village was being devastated by cancer.


        It was all because of Knox Corporation’s nuclear power plant. Nathan had finally connected all the dots together. He now knew how Knox Corp. produced enough energy to power all of the machines in the factory. He now knew why Knox Corporation was so secretive. Most importantly, he now knew why his village’s population was plummeting so rapidly…


        The nuclear power plant’s radioactive waste was being dumped in Elmwood Village.


To be continued…
The Catalyst
By: Max Wang


Recap: In The Truth, we followed the adventures of Nathan Francis, a 23-year-old man from Elmwood Village. After joining S.O.L.A.R. (a.k.a. The Society of Liberation and Rescue), Nathan became an undercover agent to uncover Knox Corporation’s secrets and discover why his village’s population was decreasing so rapidly. During the annual factory inspection, Nathan was led into a secret room concealed behind a hidden door at the back of the factory. In this room, Nathan discovered that Knox Corp. was using a nuclear power plant to power its massive machines. He finally realized that his village’s population was dropping because Knox Corporation was dumping its radioactive waste there. Now, he was ready to denounce Knox Corp.’s crimes to the world and save his village…


Chapter 10: The Arrest


        Nathan now knew everything. He knew his company’s darkest secrets. He knew why his village’s population was dropping so substantially. Nathan’s mind was racing and he was trembling with anger and disbelief. He had never imagined that Knox Corporation would do such a sinister thing to innocent people. As he held back his anger, Nathan took a few deep breaths and attempted to regain his composure. He hid behind the other executives and listened to the chief executive’s orders. The chief told everyone to wear radiation suits and inspect the nuclear power plant. For the entire day, Nathan and the other executives monitored the plant inch by inch and recorded the temperature. At multiple points throughout the inspection, Nathan was very tempted to grab his phone and photograph all of the evidence. However, he refrained because he knew that individuals all around were actively watching him. At night, the chief executive gathered everyone and gave them a speech. He told them that the nuclear power plant’s waste was dumped every two months in an abandoned village called Elmwood Village and that no one would be harmed by the radioactive waste. After hearing this, Nathan was infuriated by Knox Corp.’s blatant lies. He quickly took out his phone and asked the chief executive to repeat what he had just said. As the chief repeated his words, Nathan started recording his words and sent them to Raynell. Now, he was sure that his plan would succeed.


        That night, as everyone fell asleep, Nathan secretly exited his camp and walked towards the factory. It was already midnight, and the factory had closed. However, there was still a squadron of SWAT guards patrolling the factory. Nathan hid behind the perimeter fence and inched his way to the back door. At the door, he swiped his ID and entered the factory. Nathan quickly navigated his way to the secret door and entered the nuclear power plant. In this plant, he proceeded to take a lot of photos, specifically of the interior and the exterior of the plant. When he was finished, Nathan snuck out of the power plant and tried to exit the building. All of a sudden though, an alarm went off! SWAT guards burst into the factory and immediately began  searching for Nathan. Nathan sprinted back inside the power plant and frantically sent the photos to Raynell. Just as he finished, the guards burst into the room. Nathen knew that he was going to be captured, so he threw his phone into the power plant’s core and prepared to die…






Chapter 11: The Evidence


At S.O.L.A.R. HQ…


        Upon midnight’s arrivals, Raynell suddenly received all of the messages Nathan had previously sent. He was surprised but nonetheless ecstatic to see that Nathan had finally cracked the code and found evidence of Knox Corp.’s illegal actions. After saving the photos and recordings into the S.O.L.A.R. database, he texted Nathan to ask how he was doing. However, after half an hour, Nathan still did not answer. He even tried to call him, but his phone was unresponsive. Now, Raynell started to panic. He knew that something must have happened to Nathan. He quickly called a meeting and informed everyone that Nathan was in grave danger. Robin was especially shaken by this since Nathan had been his best friend since kindergarten. However, he knew that there was still some hope. In addition, he also inferred that Knox Corp. would try to get information out of Nathan before executing him. Due to this, he told everyone to calm down and that he had a plan. Robin said that S.O.L.A.R. should secretly give the evidence to the government so they could rescue Nathan for themselves and arrest the heads of Knox Corp. Although the other members of S.O.L.A.R. were skeptical, they had no choice but to follow through with Robin’s plan.


3 hours later…


        Robin finished organizing all of the evidence and prepared to make the phone call. Since S.O.L.A.R. was a security and anti-crime organization, they had direct access to the phone number of the chief commander of the U.S. Army. After Robin dialed the number, his call was almost immediately answered. He introduced himself as a member of the Society of Liberation and Rescue, and he informed the chief commander of the population drop of Elmwood Village. Robin also told him that Knox Corporation was behind all of this, and showed the commander all of the evidence Nathan had gathered. The chief commander was appalled that Knox Corp. would do such a thing since three of his family members worked there. He also asked what the army could do to help resolve this situation. Robin informed him that they had an undercover agent in Knox Corp., but that he had been captured a few hours back. He also told the commander that S.O.L.A.R. wanted the army to secretly rescue Nathan and then raid the offices. The chief agreed and said that he would assign a task force to carry out the operations. Robin thanked him graciously and hung up.


Chapter 12: The Operation


U.S. Army HQ


        The chief commander immediately organized a task force after the phone call. He told them to secretly break into the offices and rescue a member of S.O.L.A.R. named Nathan. The task force he assigned was one of the best rescue forces in the entire army. It consisted of ten professionally trained officers with fifteen years of experience each. They were all armed with Vectors and MG36s and wore specially designed Kevlar suits. As they left for their mission, the chief commander informed S.O.L.A.R. and began to arrange an assault battalion.


S.O.L.A.R. HQ


        Robin and Raynell were ecstatic to hear that the task force had left but were also worried that Nathan would be executed before they arrived. They tried to gather as much information as possible and figure out where Nathan was being imprisoned. From what they knew, they inferred that Nathan was being kept on the third floor of the offices. It was where all of the confidential meetings were held, and where Knox Corp. kept all of its secret plans. It was also where the task force was headed…


The Knox Corporation Offices, Third Floor


        BANG! BANG BANG! SMASH! The gates of the offices collapsed as the specialized task force dove in. They threw smoke bombs and put on their thermal night vision goggles to see through the smoke. The offices erupted into chaos as everyone bolted out the door. The task force took advantage of this and quickly hurried up to the third floor. They broke through a steel door and entered the high-executive meeting room. There, they started searching for the place where Nathan was kept. After five minutes of inspection, they found a secret trapdoor under the meeting table. However, they didn’t immediately burst into the room. Instead, they sent down a few drones to survey the area. They found out that there was a jail room below the trapdoor reinforced with a row of turrets. The drones quickly fired at the turrets and successfully destroyed them. The task force then proceeded to open the trapdoor and approached the jail with caution. Inside, they found an unconscious man lying on the floor. The soldiers recognized him as Nathan Francis and quickly carried him out of the room. Just as they exited the room and closed the trapdoor, the alarm sounded. A message was broadcast over the intercom:


SELF-DESTRUCT SEQUENCE INITIATED
CLUSTER MUNITIONS GOING OFF IN 60, 59, 58, 57, 56, 55…
To be continued…
The Outrage
By: Max Wang


Recap: In The Catalyst, we followed the story of Nathan Francis, a 23-year-old man from Elmwood Village. After photographing evidence of Knox Corp.’s illegal activities, Nathan wastaken prisoner and locked up in the Offices. Fortunately, he was able to send all of the evidence to S.O.L.A.R. HQ. After organizing the information, Robin contacted the U.S. Army and organized a task force to rescue Nathan. The operation was successful, and the soldiers carried Nathan out of the jail cell. As they closed the trapdoor that concealed the room, an alarm suddenly went off, and a message was broadcast over the intercom:


SELF-DESTRUCT SEQUENCE INITIATED
CLUSTER MUNITIONS GOING OFF IN 60, 59, 58, 57, 56, 55…


Chapter 13: The Escape


        The task force instantaneously started bolting towards the exit. The commander ordered the strongest two soldiers to carry Nathan while the others guarded them. At half a minute, the soldiers had already arrived on the second floor, and they burst out the door with exactly ten seconds remaining on the timer for the self-destruct sequence. They hastily hopped onto their transport and sped away, while the Offices simultaneously blew up and erupted into a mushroom cloud. The booming noise woke the unconscious Nathan, and he slowly opened his eyes. The soldiers explained to him that he had been rescued and would be arriving at S.O.L.A.R. HQ in an hour. Nathan breathed a sigh of relief and closed his eyes again.
One hour later…


        The task force safely delivered Nathan to S.O.L.A.R. HQ where he was given a tearful welcome by Robin and Raynell. They all asked him how harshly Knox Corp. had treated him, and to their surprise, Nathan said that they didn’t really mistreat him in any way. However, he did say that they intended to put him in the electric chair to force out information. Thankfully, the guards arrived just in time to rescue Nathan before he was to be tortured. Afterward, the members of S.O.L.A.R. discussed the best way to denounce Knox Corp.’s sinister actions to the public. They decided that the heads of the company should be arrested first before the news came out. However, there was a slight problem: The infiltration of the Offices had alarmed the leaders, so they were now in hiding. Nathan also knew this, and he was ready to find them and bring them to justice.


        Chapter 14: The Hunt


        One fateful afternoon, Nathan called the U.S. Army headquarters and reported that he had collected key information as to the whereabouts of the leaders of Knox Corp. The night prior, he was thinking about where the heads of the company could hide when all of a sudden, he remembered something. Nathan remembered when he was just a cashier in Alpha Market, and when he didn’t know a single thing about the Knox Corporation. He could still clearly remember the day when the wall in the storage room of the market suddenly collapsed and almost crushed him. The official explanation was that the wall was ‘very old’, and that heavy rain had seeped through the roof and eroded the cement, thus causing the wall to collapse. At the time, Nathan believed this excuse, seeing as he had no other explanation. However, he had an alternative now: Hidden behind the wall was a secret room perfect for hiding people.


        After telling the chief commander about his suspicions, he was quickly assigned to a task force to investigate the whereabouts of the leaders of Knox Corp. That night, Nathan secretly infiltrated the Alpha Market alongside the task force and led them to the storage room. The soldiers quietly placed a C4 on the wall and waited for a few seconds before…BOOM! The bomb exploded and revealed a massive hole in the wall. The soldiers rushed in with XM8s while a group of soldiers carrying snipers stayed behind with AWPs. Nathan stayed in the middle with a Deagle in hand and warily entered the dark hole in the wall. As they ventured deeper and deeper, Nathan felt as though they were descending into a hideout. His suspicions were confirmed when he saw specks of light and heard shouting in the distance. The soldiers had also heard the noises, and they traced the source of the noise. Nathan followed behind, and after a minute or so, they arrived at another door. This time, however, it was adorned in decorations and vibrant paint. Nathan grasped that the leaders of Knox Corp. were most likely hiding in a room behind the door and that they were still unaware of the task force’s presence. As the commander gave a silent countdown, the soldiers readied their guns and prepared to burst in.


3…2…1…GO! GO! GO!


The soldiers and Nathan, charged in and immediately began arresting the heads of Knox Corp., one by one. They were all in shock and were horrified that the U.S. army [a][b]had come to apprehend them, so most of them simply surrendered and begged for mercy. A few others, however, were able to escape the fray and quickly disappeared down the massive hallway. The commander ordered a group of soldiers to pursue them, and Nathan immediately followed suit. He walked down to the farthest room and discovered a tunnel behind the king-sized bed. Nathan called for the members of the task force, and they accompanied him into the passage. After a while of crawling, they caught up with the fugitives and handcuffed them. The task force herded all of the convicts back into Alpha Market and intopolice cars called by S.O.L.A.R. Thus, the heads of Knox Corp. were captured, and all that Nathan needed to do was to reveal their crimes to the public.




Epilogue: 1 month later…


        Knox Corporation’s actions had been officially revealed to the public, and everyone was shocked. All of the stores Knox Corp. owned and operated were permanently shut down, and its leaders were expecting a trial soon. This scandal stayed on the breaking news list for nearly an entire month, topping the charts for the most viewed event in the 21st century.[c] S.O.L.A.R. began receiving wave after wave of media attention, and Nathan, Robin, and Raynell were awarded dozens of badges and honorable titles. However, the awards and the praise weren’t the things that made Nathan happy—instead, it was the new medicine that was developed for the people in his village who had contracted cancer because of Knox Corp.’s actions. Now, Elmwood Village was truly saved, and Nathan could finally breathe a sigh of relief. Yet, one thing remained true: Nathan Francis was a special man, with a special job, a special life, and a special past and future.[d][e][f]

Kurma: The Monk in Isolation
By: Max Wang

	A cloudless, blood red sky. Thousands of bodies litter the desert as the battle rages on. Two warriors, side by side, rush at the hooded man on the top of the sand dune. The hooded man smiles slightly and suddenly releases a fireball conjured by his magic. The two warriors quickly jump aside and continue their ascent, one grasping a sword, the other, a bamboo stick. Both of them quickly reach the peak and leap towards the hooded sorcerer. Unfazed, the sorcerer creates an invisible barrier and knocks the warrior with the sword aside, breaking his leg. Taking advantage of this chance, he rushes towards the fallen soldier, attempting to end his life. Suddenly, a projectile knocks the hooded man in the head. The other warrior had just thrown his bamboo stick, saving his comrade from death. However, he was now weaponless, and could do nothing more to help. The sorcerer cackled and said, “I’ll deal with you later. Now, where is the other creature?” With helpless eyes, the weaponless soldier looked at his friend, who lay on the ground, defenseless. His friend, however, smiled knowingly. He motioned towards the sorcerer’s back, and then looked at his own sword. Seeing what his friend wanted him to do, the weaponless soldier sprinted in the direction of the sorcerer and caught his friend’s sword just in time. With all of his might, he plunged the sword into the sorcerer’s back. SHING! The evil magician’s eyes widened in horror as he fell to the ground. The two victorious warriors were just about to celebrate when the sorcerer said his last words: 
“I may not be able to kill you, but…I will still let you pay the price.”

“CURSE YOU, YOU IMBECILE! YOU SHALL NEVER HEAL AGAIN, EVEN AFTER THE DAY HELL FREEZES OVER!”
CRACK! His eyes flew open as he jolted up from his bed. His clothes were drenched with cold sweat, and he was shaking with fear. Slowly, he took a few deep breaths, regained his composure, and trudged out of his bedroom. He was a tall monk named Kurma, with tired brown eyes and a bald head. Kurma plodded into the kitchen and whipped up his favorite meal: stir-fried vegetables with udon. After eating, he climbed up the stairs and arrived at the peak of Tai Shan. Hidden in the peaks of Tai Shan, there lies an ancient, mysterious temple, one only few knew existed. The cobblestone walls had already crumbled, and moss lined the cracked pavement. Kurma entered the small, ancient temple, situated himself on a shiny lotus throne, and started to meditate.
A few hours later…
After gaining enough life force, Kurma the monk decided to go to the village at the bottom of Tai Shan. For the last 10 years, he had tried to gain as much life force as possible by meditating. Life force was a mysterious form of energy that could only be gained by meditation (any other possible ways were exempted from Kurma’s knowledge). It would help him achieve enlightenment on the day his soul left the Earth. As he quickly descended the stairs surrounding Tai Shan (he had already done this thousand of times), he sang a funky little tune:

O my comrades, how are you,
Can you hear me sing this little tune?
May you always be in peace,
May you always be in one piece,
O do you know how much I miss you?

After singing this for 147.53 times, Kurma finally arrived at the foot of Tai Shan. He entered the small village right next to it (this village had excellent hot springs) and met up with the village elders. Usually, they talked about a variety of things, from growing crops to taking care of children, as well as politics to private matters, etc. This time, however, all of the village elders seemed very stressed. Their eyebrows were furrowed, their hands were fidgety, and they had very, very large dark circles under their eyes. Confused, Kurma asked the elders what was troubling them and if he could help. The elders ushered him inside the town hall, shut the door, and locked it. Kurma was quite surprised at the level of secrecy, and he began to realize that the situation was extremely grave. As he sat down, the elders began to address the situation.
“As you know, our king was a benevolent and kind person. He was frugal and always helped the people, no matter what. Our queen was also extremely wise, with great intelligence and a big heart. Yet, there are always vicious tyrants and corrupt officials that are blinded by their own desires. They will hurt people, use people, and even kill people to satisfy their unquenchable thirst for power and fortunes. And unfortunately, these monsters have the strongest armies in this world and will endlessly wage war on other kingdoms. Alas, our kingdom has the best economy in the world, so naturally we are their greatest target. One month ago, a mysterious tyrant marched his massive armies towards our borders. Within weeks, they crushed our walls, slaughtered our soldiers, and captured and enslaved our civilians. Just a few days ago, our king and queen got captured by the enemy, and they took control of our great kingdom. I have heard that the new tyrant has also imposed harsh laws and cruel punishments on our poor fellow citizens. Alas, alas! Our once bright, peaceful country has now become a desolate wasteland of lost and dead souls!”
	“WHAT!?” Kurma exclaimed. “How…how…no! This is not possible!” 
One of the elders shook his head and said grimly, “Well…anything is possible. Even the brightest stars may die and fade one day.” 
Kurma took a few deep breaths and attempted to calm down. He began to logically think about this problem and suddenly thought of an important question: “Village elders, I acknowledge that this is a very hopeless situation, and I am also extremely devastated. However, we must analyze the situation logically and devise a plan. To begin with, I have an important question: “Have there been any rebellions against this tyrant?”
One of the village elders answered, “This tyrant understands that the only things capable of defeating him are magic and potions. Due to this, he has started collecting energy crystals from all around the kingdom. These energy crystals are extremely powerful and are the source of the sorcerers’ powers. In addition, he has also outlawed the practice of brewing potions. Anyone caught by the royal guards will be executed, and their corpses will be thrown onto the streets to terrorize the civilians.”
	Attempting to hold his anger, Kurma asked again, “Have there been any rebellions or farmer uprisings?”
	“Alas, alas,” an elder responded. “The heroes ten years ago are now nowhere to be found. Even the two great warriors that defeated the hooded sorcerer and put our king on the throne have disappeared into the depths of the unknown.”
	“No…” Kurma thought. “How…how did our great king get captured? Did he not protect our king? Is he still not starting a revolt?” Abruptly, Kurma felt a sense of deep guilt. “I cannot blame him for not taking action. He may already be starting a silent rebellion. Alas, alas! I cannot help him, yet now I blame him! How can I slander him, my dear brother, like this!”
	Kurma’s eyes became red as he became overcome with guilt. The elders asked what was happening, but the monk knew he could not tell the truth. He said, “I am heartbroken to hear what has become of our great kingdom, yet I do not know what to do to help.”
	The village elders sighed and shook their heads. “The only thing we can do now is to try to hide our village from this cruel tyrant. We will try to disguise ourselves, but even then,I think the armies of that vicious tyrant will easily spot a village at the foot of Tai Shan.”
	Suddenly, Kurma had a great idea. He told the village elders, “I have an abundance of space in my temple, and there are also many small chapels along the stairs leading to the peak of Tai Shan. I think we may be able to house all of the villagers, although it may be a bit cramped.”
	The village elders grabbed Kurma’s hand as tears of delight streamed down their faces. “We thank you from the bottom of our hearts, O dear monk! Yet, will there be enough space in your abode? In addition, how will we get the elderly and our necessities up to the top of the mountain?
	With determination, Kurma said, “I believe that there will be enough space, and even if there is not, we can build a few more small cabins. As for the elderly and our necessities, I have a proposal: Since we have little chapels almost every 500 steps, we will first let the young and strong help us carry the necessities up the mountain on carts. Next, we will cut some wood and use it to make new cabins. Finally, when the time comes, we will escort the elderly up the mountain, taking breaks along the way. There are many trees and springs on Tai Shan, so we will not deplete our resources.”
	After hearing this, the elders could finally be at ease. With overflowing gratitude, they thanked Kurma again, and then went to meet with the villagers. It was already nighttime, so Kurma made his way up the mountain and arrived at his abode just before midnight. He trudged into his bedroom and collapsed onto his bed. He knew it was going to be extremely difficult to transport an entire village up the 5029 foot incline that was Tai Shan, but what choice did he have? With a heavy sigh, he said, “When will we meet again, my brother and comrade? How I wish I could go back to the days when we were fighting evil, side by side! How I wish…
“I could still go back to the days when I wasn’t helpless, when I was still free from that curse!”
To be continued…
Shadow Rebellion
By: Max Wang

20 Years Ago…
	“Master, what are we going to do in this room?” asked a frail, 10-year-old boy.
	“Today, we will see your potential,” said his master excitedly. “Over the centuries, us alchemists have established a tradition in which we determine a youngsters’ potential on their 10th birthday.”
	“But, master,” asked the boy worriedly, “what if I don’t have any potential?”
	“Don’t you worry,” his master reassured him kindly. “The first day I saw you when you were five, I knew you had some talent in those bones. Now, there are hundreds of supplies on these shelves. Follow your heart, your mind, and most importantly, your gut, and choose as many ingredients as you want to make a random potion.”
	“Really?” asked the boy excitedly. “So, I can use anything on these massive shelves?”
	“Yes!” his master replied. “Brew anything you want.”
	And with that, the little boy rushed into the storage and started rummaging through it. His master smiled and then exited the room.

12 Hours Later…
	It was already midnight, and the boy was still not done brewing his potion. The master started to worry about him, so he put on his hood and rushed out to find his student. Along the way, he found the little boy, who was also on his way to tell the master that he had finished.  Relieved, the master followed him into the room. To his surprise, the potion was completely clear. It looked just like water but even more transparent. Intrigued, the master took a whiff of it… and he almost fell onto the floor! It smelled… bitter, and in the world of alchemy, only the most potent, forbidden potions smelled bitter. Before the master could stop him, the little boy said, “Master, watch this!” as he drank the entire potion.
“NO!” his master cried, but it was too late. The boy… was gone! Horrified, his master called his name. “Amun? Amun!!”
“Master, I’m here!” replied the little boy, confused at why his master was fretfully calling his name.
“What… no, this cannot be!” his master murmured. Only the most potent, powerful potion… only the most skilled alchemist…”
“Master, what’s wrong! I can’t see my hands!” The little boy cried, horrified that he couldn’t see his own body.
“Ahhh… my child…” his master sighed. “Fate always surprises us in every single way possible!” He then revealed the astonishing truth.

	“Amun, you have just brewed the most potent potion in the world of alchemy, the legendary invisibility potion! You are destined to become a decider of fate, yet you must use your powers for good and survive countless dangers. I pray for your safety, but I can only help you for now…”

10 Years Later…
	“Master, what are we going to do on this hill?” asked a frail, 10-year-old girl.
“Today, we will see your potential,” said her master excitedly. “Over the centuries, us sorcerers have established a tradition in which we determine a youngsters’ potential on their 10th birthday.”
	“But, master,” asked the girl worriedly, “what if I don’t have any potential?”
	“Don’t you worry,” her master reassured her kindly. “The first day I saw you when you were five, I knew you had some talent in those bones. Now, here is an energy crystal, which is the source of our powers. We channel the energy of these crystals into our powerful spells, which range from destructive to healing ones. Here, take this one and absorb it like this.” The master made a quick hand motion, and the little girl followed suit. Immediately, the crystal dissolved, and her body absorbed the energy. “Excellent!” her master said. “Now, do any hand motion you would like, and at the end, push both of your hands out and face towards that hilltop right there.
	“Really?” asked the girl excitedly. “So, I can conjure any spell that I want?”
	“Yes!” her master replied. “Do anything you want.”
	And with that, the little girl faced the hilltop, put her hands out, and started. At first, she made some random hand motions, but then she became serious. The little girl looped her hands around each other, pulled them back, and then made a triangular shape with her thumbs and index fingers. Instantly, a triangle, circle, and square appeared, and they intertwined. Slowly, a purple ray of energy appeared, and it grew bigger and bigger until it started to engulf the little girl. “Help, master!” the little girl screamed.
	“Stay calm, stay calm!” the master said, astounded at how much energy the little girl had conjured. “Kali, if you feel like you can’t handle it anymore, push your hands forward and let go!”
	Hearing this, the little girl quickly pushed her hands forward. A huge purple beam charged into the hillside as the entire top of it exploded. Debris flew everywhere as the remnants of the hilltop came tumbling down.
	“M-m-m-master? What have I done?” the girl asked, horrified at what had just happened.
	“Ahhh… my child…” her master sighed. “Fate always surprises us in every single way possible!” He then revealed the astonishing truth.

	“Kali, you have just conjured one of the most destructive spells in the world of sorcery, the mythic comet! You are destined to become a decider of fate, yet you must use your powers for good and survive countless dangers. I pray for your safety, but I can only help you for now…”
10 Years Later…
	It was a dreary afternoon, with heavy fog that clouded the sky and blocked out the sun. Ever since the new king came, there had not been a single bright day. As people trudged towards the town square, royal guards took their positions on towers and near shops. In addition, a platoon of guards stood at every single one of the four doors, which corresponded with the four directions. Every day, the tyrant would enact new laws, and people would be forced to listen to them every day at the town square. Everyone dreaded this time of day since most of the laws were all harsh, and the punishments were extremely severe. Sometimes, a few rotting corpses would be put on stakes to terrorize the civilians! At the West door, a hooded man entered briskly, while at the East door, a hooded woman walked swiftly to the town square. They had arrived just in time to hear the new law:

“As the mayor, I hereby declare that the emperor has issued a strict ban on all alchemy and sorcery. Anyone caught practicing these forbidden arts shall be crucified and hanged on the stakes of this town square!”

	“WHAT!?” the two hooded people exclaimed at the same time. Their intense reaction caught the attention of the royal guards, and they knew at once that they had been uncovered. Although the two did not know each other, they understood that they would both be hanged if the royal guards captured them.
The hooded man said, “Here, take this speed potion and let’s bolt towards the North door!” Together, the two drank the potion and sprinted towards the gate, while the royal guards tried to stop them. However, the effects of the speed potion were too strong, and the soldiers couldn’t catch up with them. After running for ten minutes straight, the two finally stopped and panted for breath. Gasping, they told each other their true names and their background. The hooded man talked first and said, “My name is Amun, and I am an alchemist. I know how to brew many different potions, but the more powerful they are, the longer they take to brew. Right now, I am brewing a shield potion, which can protect us, but it will still take around five minutes. I have a jump potion ready, though, so we can use it now.”
The hooded woman said, “My name is Kali, and I am a sorceress. I can conjure a variety of spells, and my strongest one is a destructive comet that can destroy mountains in one blast if I charge it long enough. However, I need alchemy crystals to conjure my spells, and I only have three left.”
“Ahhhh…” sighed Amun. “I guess we are in a grave situation right now. Anyway, let’s get some provisions and escape this horrid place.”
“Agreed,” said Kali, and together the two set off to buy some provisions.

2 Hours Later…
	After eating a hearty brunch, the duo set off on their journey to the north. When they were just about to exit the large gate that led to a major trading route, suddenly, a large group of royal guards charged towards them. “Ahhh…” murmured Kali. “I guess we will have to fight our way out of this.”
	Amun replied, “There are too many royal guards. Let’s take a cut and hide in the wilderness.” And with that, the two sprinted into the woods, with the guards in hot pursuit. The speed potion’s effects had already worn off, so Kali and Amun were losing ground. Just when the soldiers were about to catch up, Kali conjured a blast and destroyed a few trees behind them. This blocked the path of the royal guards, so they had to dismount their horses and chase on foot. After a few minutes of non-stop running, the duo reached a dead end. They had ended up on a treacherous cliff, and there were clusters of sharp rocks directly beneath them.
	As the royal guards slowly approached, their leader shouted, “Die or come with us to die! The choice is yours!”
	Kali whispered, “Amun, do you still have the shield and jump potion?”
	Amun replied, “Yes, I do,” and handed her the potions.
	They drank both of them, and Kali yelled, “Brace for impact!” She charged up a huge purple comet and blasted at the cliff. Instantly, it exploded as Kali and Amun were blasted backward. They were protected by the shield potion, and the jump potion increased the explosion impact, so they successfully avoided the sharp rocks. The duo plummeted down thousands of feet and into the ocean with a monstrous, deadly crash. The guards, who presumed that they were dead, retreated back into the woods. As for Kali and Amun, all that was left of them was their two identical hoods, floating on the vast, empty ocean.

To be continued…
Horn of Justice
By: Max Wang

	Arcane Falls was a town at the foot of the largest waterfall in the kingdom, hence its name. Mist covered valleys surrounded the peaceful village, and a long, twisted river ran through the mountains, providing the inhabitants with fresh water and silt. This made Arcane Falls excellent for farming, and there was always an abundance of food after the annual harvest. The town was led by the Council of the Five Elders, and they organized the town so well, it developed from a few hundred people to around ten thousand people. The leader of the elders, interestingly, was also the youngest of them all: Enzo.

Ten years ago, a mysterious hooded figure arrived in the town, and he began as an artisan who made pottery. Slowly, he began to interact with the people in the town, and everyone thought he was a cordial, respectful neighbor. He introduced himself as Enzo, and said that he used to be a soldier for the benevolent king. As the years passed, Enzo became involved with the political affairs of Arcane Falls, and he quickly became known as a responsible and outspoken leader. In the fifth year he arrived at the town, Enzo became elected as one of the elders of the town. This was an extremely wise decision, as his leadership led the small town to new, unimaginable heights. He noticed that the town produced an abundance of food, and so he distributed thirty percent of it to storage and exported the rest. This opened a major trading route that passed through Arcane Falls, and the town soon became extremely prosperous from all of this trade. This also caused the population to skyrocket, and many skilled artisans and craftsmen flocked to the town for job opportunities. Furthermore, Enzo generously offered high wages to scholars, and soon enough, hundreds of scribes and educators immigrated to Arcane Falls, improving the education and public facilities. Finally, the wise leader took advantage of the geographical location of the town, and he actively advertised the town as a beautiful natural wonder. This attracted many tourists to Arcane Falls, which further benefited the economy. In a matter of five years, Enzo had become one of the most respected people in the town, and in another five years, he had turned Arcane Falls into a major trading center with advanced education and hundreds of tourists.

The Winter of the Tenth Year…
	“Sir, sir!” A scribe frantically rushed into the city hall, carrying a thick scroll.
	“What happened, Peter?” asked Enzo worriedly.
	“Sir, I just received a letter from my friend at Tai Shan, and it is directed to you. When I saw the cover title though…” Peter turned away, frightened, and he shoved the letter into Enzo’s hands. Enzo looked at the cover of the letter, and immediately turned white. It said:
Beware, beware! Our city walls have been breached, and our King has been captured!
	“WHAT!!?”exclaimed Enzo. The letter dropped on the floor as his hands trembled uncontrollably. “No…n-n-n-no…NO! My king! How…how…” and with that, tears streaked down his face as he fell off his chair and collapsed onto the floor, unconscious.

A few hours later…
	“Sir…sir! You finally woke up!” Peter exclaimed, delighted.
	“No…no…” Enzo covered his face with his hands and groaned painfully. “Tell me the whole story, Peter.”
	With an anguished expression, Peter told Enzo everything that had happened. “As you know, our king was a benevolent and kind person. He was frugal and always helped the people, no matter what. Our queen was also extremely wise, with great intelligence and a big heart. Yet, there are always vicious tyrants and corrupt officials that are blinded by their own desires. They will hurt people, use people, and even kill people to satisfy their unquenchable thirst for power and fortunes. And unfortunately, these monsters have the strongest armies in this world and will endlessly wage war on other kingdoms. Alas, our kingdom has the best economy in the world, so naturally we are their greatest target. One month ago, a mysterious tyrant marched his massive armies towards our borders. Within weeks, they crushed our walls, slaughtered our soldiers, and captured and enslaved our civilians. Just a few days ago, our king and queen got captured by the enemy, and they took control of our great kingdom. I have heard that the new tyrant has also imposed harsh laws and cruel punishments on our poor fellow citizens. Alas, alas! Our once bright, peaceful country has now become a desolate wasteland of lost and dead souls!”
	Without a word, Enzo suddenly rose from his bed and strode to his huge closet. As he opened the two wooden doors, he pressed a button hidden behind his clothes. Slowly, the back of his closet slid open, and a blinding light emitted from it. With blazing eyes, Enzo removed the two artifacts that he had kept hidden from the day he arrived at Arcane Falls. He pulled out an elegant sword with engravings on it and a huge, intricately designed war horn. These two objects emanated a stunning bright light, yet Enzo was unfazed. He unsheathed his sword, and read the words engraved on it: “The victor is not victorious unless the vanquished considers himself so.” He then blew his horn which unleashed a beautiful yet terrifying sound, and yelled into the sky, “Veni, vidi, vici!” Instantly, the ground shook, the mist in the valleys cleared, and the water in the river overflowed, splashing the fields. Enzo sighed with relief and said, “I guess it's time I go back to WAR.”

A few hours later…
	“Elders of the Council! I have called this meeting to discuss some breaking news. As you all probably know by now, the walls of our kingdom have been breached, and our benevolent king and queen have been captured. This new tyrant is extremely cruel, and his royal guards are searching for villages to conquer everywhere. From today on, we will never be safe from that tyrant, and so I have a daring proposal. I will personally start and lead a rebellion against that tyrant!”
	“What!? Enzo, are you out of your mind?” The oldest elder exclaimed. “If we start a rebellion right now, we will just be jumping into a pit of fire!”
	Already expecting this, Enzo explained, “My dear elders, our king and queen were the most benevolent rulers we have ever had. They strengthened our economy, made our country peaceful, and did a hundred times more than what I did. Yet, when that vicious conqueror came, our king was defenseless, as none of us had the power to defend against that tyrant’s ferocious royal guards. However, he has one great weakness: His harsh laws and cruel punishments have caused outrage amongst the people, and they are all waiting for someone to liberate them. As the center of a major trade route, Arcane Falls has everything needed to start a rebellion–people, food, provisions, etc. As for how to carry out this operation, I have an artifact that will aid us.” And with that, Enzo pulled out his large war horn and blew it. He yelled, “Veni, vidi, vici!” Instantly, the ground shook, the mist in the valleys cleared, and the water in the river overflowed, splashing the fields. Suddenly, all of the elders felt a rush of confidence, a sense that they could do anything and stop evil. With pride, Enzo said, “Elders of the Council, I present to you…the Horn of Justice.”

	The Next Day, Town Square…
	“Settle down, everyone, settle down! Our fellow elder Enzo has something to say to you all.” The Elders of the Council stepped aside as Enzo walked to the center.
	“My friends! As you all know, our great king has been captured, and our city walls have crumbled like sand, all because of a vicious tyrant. His laws are harsh, his punishments cruel, and he has also doubled our taxes! Throughout our country, citizens like you are dying on the streets, either starved to death or hanged on stakes. In a matter of time, that desolation will also sweep our peaceful town of Arcane Falls, and we will all be devastated by the tyrant’s fierce royal guards!” An outbreak of distress and outrage erupted in the large crowd gathered around Enzo. Smiling to himself, he continued. “Will we let this tyrant win? No! Will we let him sweep our lands and take away everything that we love? No! Will we let him slaughter us, one by one, until we all fall under the sword of his royal guards?”
	“NO!!” The crowd screamed in unison.
	“Then, let us rise together! Together, we will fight for our freedom, fight for our kingdom, and fight for our families. Today is the day in which we stop this cruel tyrant from taking everything away from us. Call your brothers and sisters, tell everyone you see: We will not stand for this injustice anymore! The oppressed shall rise, and nothing will stop us. The people outnumber the guards one thousand to one, and together, with our united will, we shall conquer anything that stands in our fight for freedom, for justice. Arise, my brethren, arise! VENI, VIDI, VICI!” The crowd erupted into cheers as the people started chanting, “VENI! VIDI! VICI!” In the midst of this, Enzo raised the Horn of Justice and blew as hard as he could. An arousing sound swept over the people, and they all felt a strong feeling of confidence and passion, a sense of motivation for a better future. The elders, impressed with how well Enzo could lead the people, immediately gave him permission to start gathering people for the rebellion, and they also began to prepare for battle.
	After giving his speech, Enzo immediately started to spread word of the rebellion and attract potential recruits. Since Arcane Falls was the center of a major trade route, Enzo took advantage of this opportunity and notified all of the traders who came to the town. The traders then went back to their hometowns and told everyone there about it too. In a matter of a few weeks, almost half of the entire kingdom knew about the rebellion. This, however, also attracted the attention of the royal guards. Thankfully, Enzo was able to know of this beforehand, and he deceived the leader of the royal guards by disguising the town. They were tricked into believing that Arcane Falls was just advertising for the annual harvest. After enough people had been attracted by this call to arms, Enzo spread the word that he would be giving a speech talking about the rebellion on the night of the harvest. That day, tens of thousands of people flocked to Arcane Falls to hear Enzo’s speech. There, Enzo gave the same speech, but he made it longer and included living, relatable examples. At the end, while the crowd was chanting “VENI, VIDI, VICI”, Enzo raised the Horn of Justice and blew it again. This time, with so many people supporting Enzo, the sound of the horn blasted across thousands of miles, even going as far as the capital. The sound aroused the spirits of the crowd and gave them a strong boost of confidence and motivation. This time, even the fainthearted were not afraid to start a rebellion. 
That night, Enzo started to recruit soldiers for the army. In a matter of a few weeks, he had already amassed an army of nearly 50,000 dedicated rebels. He meticulously planned an army formation based on how skilled each recruit was, and Enzo was even able to find a few experienced generals. Every day, he woke up at 5:00 and trained the troops, day and night. In a short amount of time, he had already built a standing army from scratch. It consisted of 30,000 fierce infantry, 10,000 swift cavalry, and 10,000 accurate archers. Enzo’s arsenal was composed of 30,000 swords and shields, 10,000 spears, 10,000 crossbows, and more than 500,000 arrows. He had acquired all of these weapons from a distant village in the mountains, which specialized in metal workings. Finally, Enzo received all of his provisions from his own town of Arcane Falls, as this year’s harvest had produced a much larger surplus than usual. In the spring of Enzo’s eleventh year at Arcane Falls, he set off with his men on a journey to the North. With around a thousand ships provided by the islanders of Xenoxia, his army set sail from the river that wrapped around Arcane Falls. For days, they sailed through the mountains, enjoying the pleasant sight of the rolling hills and countless valleys. On the fifth day, Enzo’s army had finally arrived at the vast ocean, with him at the front of the fleet. That day, as the sun reached its peak, his scouts reported that they had spotted two black dots amidst the vast ocean. Confused, he urged his men to go forward at full speed, and he was greeted by a horrifying sight. The two black dots were actually two bodies, floating on the empty ocean. Frantically, Enzo’s soldiers quickly found a rope and tied a skilled sailor to it. They lowered him slowly until he could reach the two bodies, and one by one, he rescued them from the ocean. The soldiers brought the two unconscious figures to Enzo, and he immediately ordered the ship nurse to find rooms to accommodate the two rescued people, who were still in a coma. After that, Enzo continued to set sail on the ocean and advance to the North.
That night…
	As the night crew, composed of twenty people, were getting ready to take the deck, Enzo returned to his captain’s quarters to rest. Before sleeping, however, he quietly entered the sick bay to check up on the two rescued victims, who were still in a comatose state. Sighing, he sat beside them and checked their temperature. They're recovering, Enzo thought to himself as he took out his legendary Horn of Justice. Gently, he blew a soothing sound that rejuvenated the spirits of the sailors and also the two unconscious bodies. Slowly, they opened their eyes and groggily asked each other if they were in good shape. Enzo, startled that they had already woken up, hurriedly introduced himself and his ship. The two mysterious people sat up and intently listened to his story. As he finished, Enzo said, “...and that's what's been happening. Now, I am also quite curious to know who both of you are and your backstories.” Smiling, the duo introduced themselves.
	The man said, “I am Amun, and I am an alchemist.” The woman said, “I am Kali, and I am a sorceress.”
