Kurma: The Warrior of Immortality
By: Max Wang

Recap: On Tai Shan, there lived a monk named Kurma. He used to be a war veteran with his brother, and they defeated an evil sorcerer in order to put their own king onto the throne. Yet, before the sorcerer died, he cursed Kurma and removed his regenerative abilities. Due to this, Kurma hid his identity and became a monk on Tai Shan. One day, as he was visiting the village at the foot of Tai Shan, he received news that a vicious tyrant had taken over their kingdom and captured their king. The elders were also extremely worried that the tyrant would find their village and conquer it too. Kurma quickly devised a plan to transport the entire village to his abode on Tai Shan. First, he let the young and strong help him carry the necessities onto Tai Shan on carts. Next, they cut down some wood and built many new log cabins. Finally, Kurma and the villagers got ready to escort the elderly up the mountain. Yet, just as Kurma set foot on the stairs, a large commotion erupted behind them…

	“THE GUARDS ARE HERE!!” yelled the villagers in unison.
“WHAT?!” Kurma exclaimed. “No…this cannot be!” Hundreds of royal guards on swift horses stampeded towards the crowd as the elderly desperately tried to run away. Kurma, knowing that he would certainly die if he fought the guards, sprinted up the mountain to call for reinforcement. He quietly slipped away as the elderly were mercilessly pinned onto the ground and tied up. In around ten minutes, he arrived at his abode and told all of the villagers about the critical situation. Immediately, everyone rushed down the mountain with pathetic sticks and rocks that wouldn’t even dent in the royal guards’ armor. Kurma rushed into his house and retrieved something that he vowed he would never use again: his bamboo stick that he used in the war against the evil sorcerer. With renewed vigor, he sprinted down the mountain and quickly caught up with the rescue squad. Together, they rushed down the stairs and leaped towards the unsuspecting guards…and started whacking them with sticks and stones. The guards just laughed and laughed as Kurma snuck up behind them and smashed the ground with his bamboo stick. Instantly, five guards were knocked unconscious, and the rest were blown back by the supersonic force. Horrified, the guards backed up as Kurma charged towards them… and found that hundreds of royal guards had already surrounded him. With their superior numbers, the guards advanced towards him. Although Kurma used the supersonic attack again, one of the soldiers was still able to approach Kurma and stab him in the back. Kurma spit out blood from his mouth as he kneeled in agony on the floor. Suddenly, a flurry of rocks pummeled the royal guards as they turned away from the doomed monk. Taking advantage of this, Kurma slipped away into the forest with his last bit of strength. He collapsed beside a tree with anguish and knew that it would be his final resting place. As tears streamed down his face, Kurma let out all of the life force he had stored for ten years. With both regret and hope, his soul slowly left his body as rays of enlightenment shone through the clouds…
	
Suddenly, Kurma began to regain his consciousness. Confused, he looked down at his body… and discovered that his wound was gone! Bewildered, he looked up and saw that the rays of enlightenment were gathering in one spot. A piece of parchment slowly descended from the nine skies and rested on the ground next to Kurma. He quickly picked it up and read it aloud:



O Kurma,
‘Tis not the time for you to depart from this wretched yet beautiful world. There are still many evils that you must vanquish and even more trials that you must face… yet this time, you will not be helpless, nor will you be alone. The life force within you is a mysterious, potent form of energy that can be converted into unimaginable power. With it, you can heal yourself in the midst of battle, and you can also heal others. In addition, you can use your life force to greatly empower your attacks. Apart from meditation, you can also gain life force by doing justice, such as protecting the villagers from harm. In the near future, you will meet many new friends and foes, and you will eventually reunite with your brother, who in fact is already starting a rebellion. Remember at all times, Kurma: Be steadfast and loyal, and never succumb to darkness. In the face of evil, seek justice, and reinforcements will always come your way. Farewell, O Warrior of Immortality. With the proper decisions, you will arrive at unimaginable heights!
Sincerely,
The Watcher of the Nine Skies

	After reading this, Kurma felt a rush of enlightenment and courage, and he knew he was ready to take down the royal guards. As he was about to set out on his journey for justice, he suddenly heard a majestic, arousing sound that gave him a strong feeling of confidence, passion, and a sense of motivation for a better future. Kurma recognized that sound… in fact, he was the first to ever hear that sound… “My brother!” Kurma exclaimed in delight. “If the Horn of Justice still lives… then a massive rebellion shall be starting soon! Wait for me, O brother! I am coming!” He sprinted out of the woods and was met with a horrifying sight. The royal guards were ruthlessly chaining the villagers and shoving them into cramped cages. With fury that had been suppressed since the day he heard about the tyrant, Kurma channeled a huge amount of life force into his attack and slammed his bamboo stick as hard as he could onto the ground. Instantly, the impact produced a sonic boom, causing a major disturbance in the fault line, generating a level 5 earthquake. The royal guards were all blasted back hundreds of meters and into the woods, where they lay unconscious. Surprisingly, the villagers were unfazed by Kurma’s attack, and none of them seemed to be affected by the earthquake. Quickly, he rescued the villagers and brought them to the foot of Tai Shan. Unfortunately, the earthquake destroyed some of the stairs leading to his home, and so the villagers were left stranded. Abruptly, rays of enlightenment shone from the nine skies again, and another parchment arrived. It said:
O Warrior of Immortality,
It seems that you have indeed made this power your own. You must be wondering why the villagers were not harmed by your attack. This is because life force only damages people that should be damaged, and the extent of the damage also varies based on the individual. Some of the royal guards that you attacked will be unconscious for three days, while others will wake up in a few minutes. This is because some of them wanted to help the tyrant, while others were innocent villagers forced to join the military. Although your attacks have unimaginable power, Kurma, remember to conserve your life force and meditate often. You can also use your life force for movement, which will be particularly useful for the situation you are in right now. Now, as a final thought, remember to always be humble and treat everyone equally with respect and kindness. Everyone can harness the power of life force, yet they have to be taught by someone… like you.
Sincerely,
The Watcher of the Nine Skies
	
With this enlightenment, Kurma channeled his life force into his bamboo stick and used it to weave the shape of a dragon. Just as he finished, a huge eastern spirit dragon produced by his life force appeared and roared into the sky. Grinning, Kurma told the villagers to hop on, and they made a majestic ascent onto Tai Shan.
	
	After everyone settled into their new homes, Kurma began to search for recruits to spread the teachings of life force. Immediately, every person in the village volunteered to become his students. Even the elderly joined, as life force could reduce aging. Day after day, Kurma taught them how to meditate and channel their energy into power. He also taught them wise lessons and the importance of justice and karmic retribution. After a few months of training, Kurma had already amassed a few talented youths who were able to break trees without even touching them. In addition, he had also taught the rest of the villagers how to heal their own wounds and also slightly empower their attacks.

	In spring, Kurma decided to set out on a journey to rescue his king and defeat the cruel tyrant. Along with him, he brought his most talented students and forty other loyal students. Together, they became the Fifty Monks of Tai Shan, with Kurma being the Master of Life Force and his most talented students being the Nine Dragons, each representing a different sky.

	A few days into their journey, the Fifty Monks arrived at the seaside. They saw a huge fleet of ships approaching, and they also saw that the leader of the army was carrying a sword that emanated a stunning bright light. Kurma was seemingly unfazed by the bright light, and he murmured to himself, “What a majestic sword with a familiar gleam… could that be him?” Abruptly, an arrow whizzed above his head and snapped him out of his thoughts.
	“We are under attack!” Yelled one of the monks. Immediately, Kurma pulled out his bamboo stick and rushed to the rescue along with the Nine Dragons. Ten royal scouts were fighting with a few of the monks, but they seemed to be having no problem dealing with them, as their life force greatly empowered their attacks. Kurma told the Nine Dragons to end it quickly, and so they sent out nine air slashes created by their life force. The scouts were knocked back by the slashes, and they lay defeated on the ground. Kurma told them that he would spare their lives, but they had to lead the monks to their military base. The scouts turned out to be villagers who were forced to join the military, and so they gladly led them to their headquarters. Kurma noticed that the soldiers there were preparing fire arrows to launch at the ships, so he led the monks in a surprise attack against the royal guards. In a matter of a few minutes, the entire camp had surrendered to Kurma, and he let them go after confiscating their weapons. He looked down from the cliff and saw that the rebellion fleet was being attacked by one of the tyrant’s largest, most formidable fleets. Kurma knew that the battle would be arduous, and so he knew he had to provide help. He channeled a major portion of his life force into his bamboo stick and leaped off the cliff. As he plummeted into the water, he plunged his weapon into the depths and released all of the power stored inside. Instantaneously, it created a 6-degree earthquake, thus causing a large tsunami to sweep the enemy fleet. The rebellion fleet took advantage of this and charged forward, demolishing the royal guards. After all of the ships had been obliterated, the lead ship sailed towards Kurma as he erupted out of the water while riding on a spirit dragon. The leader of the rebellion walked to the front of the ship and shouted, “I am Enzo, leader of the rebellion! Who are you, O mighty warrior?”
	With tears brimming in his eyes, Kurma exclaimed, “O honorable Enzo, I am your brother Kurma!”
