Child of the Void	
By: Max Wang

A dark, dreary night,
With no moon in sight.
In the shadows of an abandoned alleyway,
A little girl shivers in her rags, trying to survive another day.
No family, no love,
They had all been disposed of.
She screams into the night, to no avail,
Ready to end this torturous tale.
With nothing but bread crumbs,
To the dark she succumbs.
With only a rusted knife and a ripped-out soul,
Living day by day is just an endless black hole.
She smiles, for once, and raises the knife,
Her heart is no longer able to see the light.
With only hatred for this wretched world,
She plunges into the underworld.
Before she left, she made one wish:
CURSE THIS WORLD, MAY IT FOREVER SINK INTO AN ENDLESS ABYSS!
…
…
And there went the little girl,
Another cursed, wretched soul.
A once kind heart, young and bright,
Darkness came and sucked out the light.
The cruel tyrant, cold and harsh,
Turned this kingdom into an abandoned marsh.
It was prosperous, once upon a time,
It used to be so sublime.
The girl’s body crashes to the ground,
It makes an eerie, crackling sound.
The bones crack, the blood drips,
All in the wake of a solar eclipse…
…
From the depths, the ground shakes,
Signifying the void dragon’s wake.
It bursts out of the ground, revealing an endless abyss,
Letting out a terrifying, monstrous hiss.
It swallows the body, and drags it down,
Into the abyss and beneath the ground…
…

	The void dragon rested the girl’s body on the ground and flew into a deep cave. In a few minutes, it returned with many alchemy crystals. The dragon drew the power out of the crystals and channeled it into the girl’s body. Slowly, her eyes opened, and she let out an agonizing scream due to the pain. Yet, she looked at the terrifying beast with a dull expression, not the least afraid. The void dragon opened its monstrous mouth and roared. “Why are you not afraid of me, puny child?”
	“You have revived me, and I have no will to live. Why would I be afraid?” The girl muttered.
	Abruptly, the void dragon laughed. “Hahaha! Indeed, I have found the right one. You have earned my respect, and your intentions are the same as mine. I offer you a deal: If you become my vessel, I will grant you with the power of the void. With it, you will reach unimaginable heights, including… killing anyone, including the one you wish to tear limb from limb!”
	“Yes…” The girl said, her dull eyes letting out a dark glow. “Yes! Grant me the full power of the void! Allow me to return to that wretched world, allow me to massacre those imbeciles!”
	And with that, she was consumed as she fainted on the ground…
…
	“Ughh…” The girl stood up and stretched her limbs. She took a deep breath and knew instantly that she would never be the same again. She felt the power coursing through her limbs as she let out a terrifying scream.
	“Calm down…” A voice in her head echoed. “Now, down to some important matters. I must first apologize that I have not even introduced myself. I am Kháos, χάος in Greek, and I am the last void dragon. Our species had been defeated by the sorcerers due to a dispute over alchemy crystals, and they banished us from ever returning to the Overworld. Thus, I need a vessel to exit the Void, which is you. Together, we can conquer anything and everything. I see that your intention is to kill the tyrant, and my intention is to kill the sorcerers. So, why don’t we kill them both, together as a team? Now, may I ask you to introduce yourself? There is no need to speak, as we can communicate with our thoughts.”
	“I am Aella,  Ἄελλα in Greek, and…” Suddenly, tears streamed down her face and she kneeled onto the ground. “I…used to be so happy…when my family…was still alive. I was once from a middle class family, and we made a stable income on trading. I went to school and made many friends, and it seemed like that there would be eternal peace and prosperity. Yet that tyrant came…our city was devastated by his merciless guards; shops were raided, schools were destroyed, and people were brutally massacred. And…” Aella pounded her fists on the cold, hard ground. “My parents and all of my friends were killed right in front of me! My school was bombarded by cannonballs, and my parents were hung on stakes because they traded alchemy crystals. I must take my revenge, I must tear that tyrant limb from limb! Vengeance shall be mine, and it shall be served in cold blood.” And with that, she transformed into a void dragon and flew towards the Overworld.
Three days later…
	“Kháos! I understand that I have immense power, but why do I not have tracking abilities? It’s been three days, and I have not seen a single royal guard, much less a sorcerer!”
	“Calm down, for Void’s sake! I know that you are desperate for blood, but you really need to think strategically. Why are you even searching in an abandoned forest? Do you really think that we will find any – wait. I sense… alchemy crystals… which means there is a sorcerer nearby. Get ready, it is time to kill…”
	“Why are we killing sorcerers? They didn’t do anything to me.”
	“They didn’t do anything to you, but they banished the void dragons! Now, if you want to keep your powers, go kill that sorcerer, and I will help you kill that tyrant.”
	“Fine.” Aella muttered and crept towards a rustling bush. Her left eye emitted a dark purple glow, and she swung her left hand. Instantly, she summoned a void dragon claw that teared in the direction of the bush. Kchhh! Blood dripped on the ground as the bush was sliced into pieces.
	“Nice, nice. Now, where is the body?” Asked Kháos.
	“I don’t know. I presume it must be –” Aella’s thoughts were interrupted by a powerful, magically charged punch in the face. A normal person’s skull would have been shattered by this blow, but Aella was simply knocked back, unfazed. The sender of the punch was a figure shrouded in a black hood, and there was blood dripping from their cheek.
	“Who are you, and why do you attempt to kill me!” The mysterious figure shouted. Without even speaking, Aella leaped forward and sent out another dragon claw. This time, it slammed into the ground, causing a shockwave that obliterated the nearby trees. Surprisingly, the figure was able to conjure a shield that completely negated the damage. With some distance between the two, the sorcerer absorbed an alchemy crystal and readied a powerful spell. They looped their hands around each other, pulled them back, and then made a triangular shape with their thumbs and index fingers. Instantly, a triangle, circle, and square appeared, and they intertwined. Slowly, a purple ray of energy appeared, and it grew bigger and bigger until it engulfed the sorcerer.
	“Uhhh…this sorcerer is no normal opponent. That spell looks oddly familiar…as if it was the one that killed my species!” Kháos exclaimed. “Quick, RUN AWAY!”
	Aella leaped to the side as a huge purple beam charged towards her. Instantly, the forest behind her exploded, and purple flames surged towards the sky. Her right arm was badly charred, and her dragon scale defense lowered significantly. “Ughhh…guess it’s time to end this once and for all.” Aella sprinted towards the figure and spread her arms wide. When she got close enough, she thrust her hands towards the sky, summoning a huge void dragon head from the ground. The sorcerer was pummeled into the trees, and they lay there helpless as the merciless Void Vigilante stomped towards them. Just as she was about to finish the job, a powerful kick in the stomach sent Aella flying into the sky. “WHAT!?” She exclaimed as she crashed into the forest terrain. As she stood up, another punch sent her crashing into the woods. In the distance, the sorcerer’s body was lifted up…by air? It seemed as if they were floating above the ground, which Kháos thought was extremely suspicious.
	“Aella…your dragon scales are almost done regenerating, so I advise you to go investigate what in the Void is happening.”
	Silently, Aella crept towards the body, which was still levitating in the air. Slowly but surely, she began to see that the sorcerer was not floating. Instead, they were being carried by another figure shrouded in a dark hood.
	“Who are you, and why are you tampering with our battle?!” Aella shouted.
	Before she was even able to get answers, the figure zoomed to her side at blinding speeds and sent an empowered punch, pounding her onto the ground. The figure then whizzed back and stuffed a potion into the unconscious sorcerers’ mouth. Instantly, the sorcerer was revived, and they stood next to the hooded figure.
	“Aghhh!” Aella screamed as she leaped up from the ground, furious. “Tell me your names, before I tear you limb from limb!”
	“Haha!” The hooded figure laughed. “If it’s winning battles and escaping from death, then nobody can surpass us! I am Amun, an alchemist, and this is Kali, a sorceress!” Amun motioned towards the woman next to him. “Now, who are you, and why do you stop us from defeating that cruel tyrant?”
	“What? I despise that tyrant, and I wish to kill him. Yet, the creature inside me wants that sorceress’ head, and so I must kill her. Now, step aside before I slaughter you too!”
	“Well then, let’s fight!” Kali exclaimed.
Amun handed her a rainbow potion, and said, “This potion is a mix of strength, speed, and shield that I just brewed.”
“Say less!” Kali replied, delighted. And with that, the three people charged towards each other, thus starting another epic fight. With supercharged potions, potent magic, and strength in numbers, the Shadow Rebellion was able to quickly subdue Aella.
“Well, that was pretty easy,” Amun chuckled. “Can’t believe you almost lost.”
Kali groaned, “Hey, you can’t be talking. This girl, or creature, is quite strong. So don’t let your guard-” KCHHH! Aella summoned a huge dragon head out of the ground, sending Kali and Amun flying. Thankfully, they were protected by the shield potion, or else they would have been torn into pieces. “Told you!” Kali yelled as she charged another comet. This time, Aella didn’t mindlessly charge towards the duo. Instead, she let out a terrifying scream and stomped the ground. Instantly, the sky turned dark, and a chasm opened beneath her. Kháos rose from the depths and Aella mounted him as they charged towards the Shadow Rebellion.
“Uhhh…we might be cooked, stewed, and deep-fried,” whispered Amun. Just when they were about to give up, an arousing sound swept through the forest. Kali and Amun felt a strong feeling of confidence, passion, and motivation. On the other hand, Aella heard a piercing, horrifying scream that shattered her eardrums.
“Ahhhh! What is this monstrous sound?!” screamed Aella. “Who is stopping me from tearing you both apart!”
“Not on my watch,” said a voice from behind.
“Now, who are you!?” yelled Aella in fury.
“All you need to know is that I am Enzo, leader of the rebellion, and that no one is harming my army and my friends.”
“Even if you have strength in numbers, nothing will stop me, as I have the full power of the void dragons! Every time I am knocked down, I come back stronger than ever before!” Aella said as Kháos started to charge a void beam directed at Enzo. As he released the huge purple blast, a spirit phoenix charged straight into it, creating a massive explosion which decimated the trees in the forest. BOOM! In the midst of the ashes, a figure wielding a bamboo stick appeared.
“Fear not, my friends! I have come to help!” yelled Kurma.
“Yes, brother! You arrived just in time,”chuckled Enzo.
“Wait a minute… I am sensing a mysterious and potent form of energy in that monk’s body… ISN'T THAT LIFE FORCE!? If so, then he must be from the Nine Skies… which means we should better RUN FOR OUR LIVES!” Kháos screamed inside Aella’s mind. He immediately turned his head and tried to fly away.
“Alright rebels, you all know what to do,” said Kurma. He created a spirit dragon from his life force and followed Kháos in hot pursuit. Meanwhile, Kali charged up a comet and sent it straight into Kháos’ side, which shattered his dragon scale defense. Enzo brandished the Sword of Valor and sent a light sword slash into the void dragon’s unprotected flesh. Kháos let out an agonizing scream and stopped in midair while the spirit dragon charged towards him. Kurma did a backflip and leaped off his dragon just in time to avoid the explosion that ensued after the spirit dragon crashed into Kháos and Aella. The collision of the dragons of the nine skies and the void caused a supernova that sent a sonic boom to the royal capital, 1000 miles away. Instantly, Kháos disappeared as Aella fell from the sky, unconscious and burned by the explosion. “Quick, Amun, catch her!” Yelled Kurma.
“On it!” Amun replied as he drank a speed potion and sprinted towards the doomed girl’s landing spot. In a few seconds, he carried her back to the rebels with a disgusted expression on his face. Kurma looked down at Aella and grimaced. Her left arm, which was the one she used to attack with, had been blown apart by the explosion. Her right eye had also been destroyed, so she now had a black hole in her eye socket. Kurma transferred some of his life force into Aella to keep her alive, while Amun gave her a healing potion.
“Alright, she should be fine, as void dragons are practically unkillable,” Kurma said as his head clouded with thoughts.
“So…what are we going to do now?” asked Enzo.

To be continued…

Messenger of the Wind
By: Max Wang

	“Uhhhh… I don’t really know how to proceed.” Enzo sighed.
	“Me neither.” Kali agreed.
	“How are we supposed to convince Aella?” Asked Amun.
	“I honestly don’t really know,” replied Kurma. “Fortunately, she has not woken up yet, but if she does, she most certainly will take revenge on us and attempt to slaughter Kali.”
	“Oh, bruh.” Kali shook her head. “Should we jail her up, or just end it once and for all?
	“No, we must try to save as many people as possible,” replied Kurma. “She loathes the tyrant with a passion, and with her power, our forces will be unmatched, therefore guaranteeing us a win in this war.”
	“But, my brother, how are we going to convince her? In addition, we cannot advance any further, as we do not know what treacherous forces the tyrant is hiding,” stated Enzo.1
	“Well then, I have a risky yet effective proposal. We will send a capable spy to collect information about the tyrant. Additionally, there was a rumor around camp that they once spotted a void dragon being controlled by the tyrant. If this is confirmed,  we can use the information as leverage to get Aella to give us her services to help with the rebellion,” Kurma suggested.
	“Excellent idea, Kurma. However, who is skilled and brave enough to do this?” Questioned Enzo.
	“Well, we will just have to find someone in our army,” Kurma sighed.

Later that afternoon, in the rebellion camp…

	It was a windy afternoon on the plains, but the soldiers in the camps were nice and cozy. A young soldier named Gale left the camp, as he wanted to go for a walk on the vast, beautiful great plains. Interestingly, he was never a big fan of leisurely walks, especially in the cold wind, but today, there seemed to be a mysterious force luring him out of the camp. Unbeknownst to Gale, on this fateful day, he would receive his destiny…
	
	As he strolled in the soft, tall grasses, Gale’s attention was suddenly caught by a shadow rustling in the leaves. Alarmed, he pulled out his blade and prepared to fight a wild beast, or so he thought. After waiting a while, he shook off his paranoia and continued to walk calmly. This time, however, he was much more alert.. A few minutes later, the shadow presented itself to Gale once again. Gathering his wits, he began to give chase to the entity, and unknowingly, he was being led further from his camp. A guard witnessed this, calling out to him to come back, yet Gale could not hear him. As he chased the figure, the winds began to get more and more intense. Gale was almost knocked down by the howling winds, but he quickly went back on hot pursuit. Abruptly, a sudden yet strong torrent of wind tore at Gale, pushing him aside, and he was sent tumbling. Unfazed and determined, Gale got up again and sprinted towards the shadow. Despite the fact that his stamina was starting to wear thin, his sheer will pushed through, and he began one last final sprint towards the figure. Although the immense currents were beating him back, he was able to gain ground on the figure. When he was right behind the entity, Gale leaped and caught… nothing? He collapsed on the ground, gasping for air, as he looked at his empty hands. He looked into the sky, and the winds were calm and comfortable, a warm autumn breeze. Gale couldn’t believe it. All this time, he was just hallucinating, and he nearly ran a marathon to chase a shadow of his imagination. As he cursed himself for being stupid, he walked back toward his camp, which was just a line on the horizon. The sun began to set, and Gale knew he would most definitely be late for dinner. As if he were controlled by a mysterious force, he turned and went back to the spot where he had last seen the shadow.  Abruptly, Gale's body became limp, and his body started levitating above the ground as if someone was lifting him by magic. Moments later, his eyes became gray, and he took out his sword and planted it in the ground. Instantly, howling winds began to rise, and they swirled around his sword. Gale was lifted into the air, and before he even knew what was happening, he disappeared inside his sword…

	Slowly, Gale opened his eyes, and he was shocked to see that he was surrounded in all directions by howling winds. They arranged themselves in a huge, destructive swirl, and Gale knew that it was a hurricane. However, he was in a surprisingly calm area of the storm with no winds at all. He realized that there was only one possibility: He was in the eye of a hurricane. Just then, he noticed that his sword was floating in midair, and he touched it. Instantly, a hooded figure jumped out of the sword. Gale stumbled back, yelling in shock, as he leaped and punched the figure straight in the face. However, like before, Gale felt that he had just stuck his hand through the wind.

	“Woah, calm down!” Yelled the hooded figure, who didn’t seem surprised at all for being in the eye of a hurricane.
	“Who are you, and why did you bring me to this place?” Demanded Gale.
	“Yes, you must have a lot of questions, and I will answer them, one by one. But first, to some more pressing matters. Who gave you this sword?
	“My sword? It’s my most precious possession, passed down to me by my father before he passed away. His last words were for me to inherit his sword and oppose all of the evil in the world.”
	“Well then, I believe these were not his final words, am I correct?”
Gale gasped. “How-how do you know?” After pausing for a moment, he said, “Indeed, those were not his final words. My father told me to tell this to the person who asked for his last words: O great gods, alas, I have failed you! I did not fulfill my destiny! Yet, I have a son who has great willpower and speed, and I believe he will be the Messenger we have been waiting for. As for me, may the wind carry my body away, and may my eyes be open forever, as I can never rest in peace because I have failed to fulfill my destiny.”
The mysterious figure recoiled in shock. “No! How can he say such a thing? Fate is an unpredictable thing, and he has already done so much good in the world…”
“Ummm…” muttered Gale, “Do you know my father?”
“Yes, I did. I knew him very well,” replied the figure. “Now, I think it is time to tell you who you are. You are the son of a Gust, a person destined to become the Messenger. You, your father, and I are all blessed by the wind, a natural force with unlimited bounds. Yet, only a few in these millennia have been able to fully harness the difficult power of the wind. Your father said that you had great willpower, and I saw some of that when you were chasing the shadow, which was in fact me. I am a Breeze, and I reveal to Gusts their identities and tell them their destiny. Now, it is time for me to tell yours. You will become a spy and messenger for the rebellion, relaying messages and information about the tyrant’s secret forces. If you are able to harness the power of the wind, you will be able to fulfill your destiny and overthrow the tyrant.” Slowly, the hurricane began to calm, and the Breeze started to fade away.
“Wait!” Yelled Gale frantically. “I still have a thousand unanswered questions!”
“Young one, you know the wind cannot stay still for long, and that there are no breezes in hurricanes. Good luck, Gale, or should I say, Messenger of the Wind. Fulfill your destiny, seek justice, and firmly oppose all evil! May the wind be your guide…” The Breeze disappeared, and Gale was sucked into his sword again…

Gale awoke on the great plains again, in the exact same spot where he had left. He looked into the sky with wonder and amazement, and slowly pulled his sword out of the ground. Ecstatic to try out his new powers, Gale brandished his sword in the air, trying to control the wind, but to no avail. Frustrated, he drove it into the ground, causing the winds around him to swirl and eject outwards, producing a shockwave. Startled and astonished, he took a deep breath and flourished his sword once more. This time, however, he raised it into the sky. Howling winds began to gather around the tip, and after Gale thrust the sword forward, it sent a potent wind blast which left a dent in the ground. Stunned at his newfound power, his sword clanged on the ground, and he nearly fell to his knees. After waking up from his stupor, he finally noticed that it was night. Calmly, he began to walk back to his camp again, this time without turning back. Suddenly, Gale had an excellent idea. Once again, he summoned the winds, but instead of thrusting it forward, he thrust it backward. As expected, he was blasted forward and fell face-first into the ground. Now walking with a bruised face, he grinned, finding a sense of satisfaction with his little experiment. Afterwards, he continued the same procedure of summoning the winds, but this time, he gently positioned his sword backwards. Amazingly, the winds pushed him forward, and he cruised through the sky at any speed that he desired. In no time, Gale arrived at his camp and quietly slipped into the large crowd gathered outside. It seemed that the rebellion leaders had assembled all of the troops to call for a vital meeting. The esteemed leader Enzo stepped onto the stage, and the soldiers began to cheer and hoot, including Gale. Enzo, welcoming the applause with a nod of his head, began his speech. “My fellow soldiers and friends, I have called for this meeting to announce a plan that my brother Kurma and I have devised. As you all know, our rebellion has been going quite well, yet we still cannot advance onto the tyrant’s capital. We do not know what treacherous forces he hides,  so blindly charging in would be foolish. As many of you have heard from rumors, we recently captured a demon. However, the demon is in fact a girl who has a pact with the last void dragon. She also resents the tyrant, and with her power, our victory will almost be inevitable. Thus, we must try to gather enough information from the capital to persuade her to join our cause.” The crowd of soldiers began to whisper amongst themselves, as they were uncertain what Enzo was planning. Smiling, he continued. “Under these circumstances, Kurma and I have agreed to send a capable spy to collect information from the tyrant’s capital. Yet, this mission is, without a doubt, incredibly hazardous. Only the most courageous and skilled warriors can qualify. So, who is up for this challenge?” Instantly, the soldiers erupted into heated conversations as they predicted who would be the one to embark on this dangerous, if not suicidal, mission. However, one soldier didn’t participate in any of these conversations. As soon as Enzo announced his plan, Gale confidently strode to the front of the crowd, and as he walked, the soldiers stepped out of his path, just like Moses when he parted the Red Sea. Enzo was quite surprised, as he didn’t think anyone would be brave enough to accept this job. He asked, “Who are you, O brave warrior? Are you not afraid of death?”
Gale answered, “O honorable Enzo, my name is Gale, and I would have never participated in this job if you had asked a day, or even a few hours ago. Yet, I recently had an enigmatic encounter with a powerful entity, who revealed to me that I have the ability to harness the power of the wind to my own desire.
“Oh? Such interesting and unexpected twists and turns that fate can subject us to. Before I send you on your way, Gale, could you show me your power of the wind?”
Gale nodded. “As you wish, sir.” With all of his willpower, Gale raised his sword to the sky and yelled. Clouds began to gather around the camp, and they swirled faster and faster, reaching incredible speeds as Gale let his power engulf the camp with immensely strong gusts. The grass on the plains was torn from the ground as the clouds poured buckets of rainwater outside the camp. Yet, the weather inside the camp was peaceful, and the winds were calm.
In awe, Enzo exclaimed, “Who are you, O mighty warrior? Have you been hiding your magnificent powers all of this time while you were in my army?”
Gale looked into the sky and laughed. “Esteemed Enzo, my honorable commander, please refrain from giving me so much respect. I had just learned of these powers today, and this was the first time I ever tried to generate a hurricane. There is only one thing I implore: please send me to be your eyes and your ears in the tyrant’s capital, and I will collect any information that you want. Please allow me to fulfill my destiny and become the Messenger my elders have been waiting for. Please.”
“Of course, Gale. You are the one I have been waiting for, and I will supply you with anything you need to complete this mission.”
“Thank you, O great commander. And for the matter of supplying me, there will be no need. All I need is my Hurricane, my blade, and my guide, the wind. ”
“Well then, it seems that you are eager to be on your way. Farewell, Gale, and we all wish you the best of luck!” Enzo and the soldiers began applauding, and amidst the cheering, Gale channeled the wind into his blade and blasted off into the night sky…

A few hours later…

It was a pitch black night, with no moon in sight. The once radiant, beautiful capital had become dreary and full of despair. People stayed in their homes, frightened of the outside world and the tyrant. Only the bravest civilians would periodically go out to buy necessities, but they would also nervously look back with every step they took. As Gale approached the town square, he saw giant pillars that dictated the tyrant’s harsh laws, and above them were rotting corpses of civilians hanged for treason. Hundreds of royal guards solemnly barricaded every entrance, yet Gale could see the fear in their eyes. Realization hit as he looked around, and it was then that Enzo’s words came back like a sharp current of wind to him. He realized that what the commander said was true: most of them were frightful, innocent civilians forced to join the military. Seeing the dreadful state in which the capital had turned into, rage and hatred filled him for the cruel, vicious tyrant. Instantly, howling winds began to rise, and as they picked up speed, they ripped apart the tyrant’s war flags. The soldiers ran to take cover nearby, and amidst the chaos, Gale silently glided overhead and headed directly towards the grand palace, his fists clenched in a fury…

	Quietly, Gale slipped into the ironically glorious palace of the cruel tyrant. As he entered through a high-arched, stained-glass window, he was furious to see that while the civilians were living in such dreadful conditions, the tyrant was living in such luxury. The walls were covered in quartz and silver, the roof and the colossal pillars were made of gold, and everything was adorned with precious jewels. In addition, diamond chandeliers with golden chains hung from the rooftop, and countless statues made out of pure gold decorated the endlessly long hallways. Gale tried to find his way around, but the palace was just too massive. After nearly an hour of searching, he finally found an immense staircase that led to a huge golden gate. He knew that it had to be a place of great importance, yet it was impossible for him to enter. Abruptly, Gale had a crazy and impossible idea: He would become the wind and enter through the gate’s cracks. He knew it wouldn’t work, but he still wanted to try. Gale channeled all of his energy into his thoughts, and amazingly, Gale felt his consciousness leaving his body and becoming one with the wind. He slipped through the cracks and entered a gigantic room made out of obsidian and gold. In the center, there was a large table with four people gathered around it. The one on the throne was the tyrant, without a doubt, but who were the other people? Gale saw that the one directly across from the tyrant was a knight holding a purple sword gleaming with power from the void. The two on the sides looked like a sorceress and a jester, and it looked as if these four were quite happy. The sorceress began speaking in a soft, deceiving voice. “My glorious king, I have excellent news to tell you. The knight went on a quest to battle a void dragon, and after he weakened it, the jester and I tamed it. I currently have it jailed up, and after a “treatment”, it is now ready to be Your Majesty’s pet. It will be absolutely loyal to you, and it will kill any enemy with a passion. With it, my king, you will be invincible!”
	The tyrant cackled. “Very well, very well! With my new “pet”, I will tear that rebellion apart limb from limb, and feed their corpses to this potent creature! What a beautiful sight that will be… I shall administer my plan very soon!”
	Gale was stunned and horrified, as he knew that void dragons possessed the power to demolish armies if they used their full strength, especially when they were not contained by a vessel. Yet, there was also some good news: if the tyrant was imprisoning a void dragon, then there would be enough information to convince Aella to join the rebellion. With enough collected information, Gale attempted to slip out of the cracks again. Yet, just as his soul entered his body, he saw that royal guards who patrolled the palace noticed him and one of them shouted to raise the alarm while the others gave chase. Gale turned pale as he needed to pull off an escape from the massive palace without alarming the tyrant. He surveyed his surroundings and saw that there was a huge window directly across from him in a long hallway. Since the guards were still one corridor away, Gale hurriedly threw on a set of gold armor for protection. As the soldiers advanced on him, Gale put on his helmet and unsheathed his trusty blade, Hurricane. He called the night currents and thrust his sword backwards, blasting him forward at high speeds. As expected, Gale crashed into the window and got flung into the night sky. Unfazed by the impact due to the armor’s protection, he quickly adjusted the positioning of the wind and soared into the night sky with all of the information he needed…

To be concluded with the finale…
Sunrise
By: Max Wang

At the rebellion camp…
	“General, general! The demon girl has awoken and is wreaking havoc in our camp!” A scout reported to Enzo with a fearful expression.
	Enzo’s eyes widened in terror. “What!? She has awoken from her wounds already?” He hastily arose from his seat and sprinted towards the site of destruction. When he got there, he was horrified to see soldiers on the ground everywhere. Thankfully, they were all alive and merely shaken by blunt force. Confused, Enzo looked into the distance and saw Aella attempting to punch the soldiers with her unwounded fist. The soldiers just dodged, as they knew they needed Aella to join the rebellion in order to defeat the tyrant. With a sigh, the rebellion leader pulled out his Sword of Valor and flicked it in the direction of the furious girl. A swift light beam was produced and struck Aella onto the ground. At that moment, the Shadow Rebellion and Kurma arrived at the scene. The heroes surrounded the Child of the Void and Kurma addressed her calmly.
	“We don’t want to harm you, and we also don’t want to imprison you. You see, we even let you rest in a comfortable, unguarded room. However, the moment you awoke, you began attacking our soldiers. Right now, I just want to ask why you are attacking them, and why you were even attacking us in the first place. What have we done to you? If we have offended you previously in any way, my friends and I will immediately apologize sincerely to you. But, we need to know the reason first.” Aella was evidently taken aback by Kurma’s statements. She was quite surprised by the kindness and humility they displayed even after her unprovoked attacks. 
Aella stood up and replied, “I attacked the sorceress because the void dragon inside me seeked revenge against sorcerers and sorceresses because they eliminated his kind many years ago. In fact, I have no grudge against them, but I must satisfy the dragon’s wishes in order for him to help me kill the tyrant.”
	As Aella explained the situation, Kurma sank into deep thought. He knew Aella would be a valuable asset to the team, but he could not allow Kali to be killed. Just as he was about to explain his dilemma, a figure descended from the sky. Gale had arrived at the perfect time with vital information, and Kurma could not have been more glad. He reported that the tyrant had a knight, sorcerer, and jester under his command, and he also said that they had recently captured and tamed a void dragon. Upon hearing this, Aella bowed to the heroes and pleaded for their forgiveness. Seeing that Kháos, the void dragon, had submitted, Kurma ecstatically granted Aella a full pardon and led her back to camp to treat her wounds. Enzo immediately gathered the soldiers and announced that they would be heading to the capital the next morning, and he also appointed Gale as the general leading the charge.
A few months later…
	For months, the army marched towards the tyrant’s capital. They strolled through the great plains, trudged across the desert, hiked the majestic mountains, waded the murky swamps, and wandered through the magnificent forests until finally, they arrived. The capital had lost its previous glow of happiness, peace, and prosperity. Streets and stalls lay deserted, the doors and windows to houses were bolted shut, and corpses were hung on stakes everywhere. In the distance, on a hill, lay a magnificent castle: the palace of the tyrant, which he had obtained through doubling taxes and imposing forced labor. With anger burning in his eyes, Enzo turned towards the rebellion army.
“My family, my friends, my people! Today is the day we arrive at this capital, today is the day of the final battle, and today is the day we defeat that tyrant and take our kingdom back!” The crowd hooted and cheered in delight. “However, the tyrant and his forces are unimaginably strong. It is without a doubt that we will suffer losses.” The soldiers looked at one another as fear flashed in their eyes. “But do not fear!” Enzo shouted. “Today, we fight for justice, and destiny will be on our side. Remember what the tyrant has done, and channel your rage, your sadness, and your hatred into an unstoppable force! From the day we started this journey, we refused to be oppressed. And so we fought hard and marched on, conquering towns by towns, cities by cities. Today is the last step of our conquest, the day our names will be cemented in history. Let us face this fateful day with unwavering courage and passion, and let us fight for our family, our friends, our kingdom, our brethren, and our future. VENI, VIDI, VICI!” As Enzo blew the Horn of Justice, the rebellion army charged at the capital with Gale as their leader.
	The army was halted by the royal guards as they approached the city gates. A cavalry of void minions riding dark horses rode to the front, and they were led by a void squire. Gale dismounted his horse and walked forward to meet him. He said, “Who are you, and why do you halt us in our path? Friend or foe, state your name first!”
	The squire said in a cold, robotic voice, “I have come to demolish the rebellion, and if you are one of them, I will slaughter you this instant.”
	Gale sighed. “I see you are about to fight us right now. However, I have an offer for you. I challenge you to a duel, and the leader who wins will be able to advance their army.”
	The void squire cackled. “No matter what happens, I will quash the rebellion. But… I would enjoy tearing you limb from limb first. I accept.”
	“Then let us begin. My friends, clear the way!” The two armies parted as the void squire and Gale stood on opposite sides of the arena.
	“Your call,” Gale shouted. Surprisingly, the void squire simply raised his hand into the sky. Confused, Gale looked around. Big mistake. An instant later, the squire summoned a blade made from void energy and lunged at superhuman speeds at Gale. Thankfully, he was able to send out a gust of wind to parry the hit, or else he would have been sliced into pieces. He quickly pulled out his Hurricane Blade and clashed with the void squire. Their swords danced as embers flashed from the impact. Gale locked blades with his opponent and held him in a stalemate. He summoned winds from all directions and blasted it from the tip of his blade, sending the void squire flying. Seeing that Gale had the upper hand, all of the void minions charged towards him, turning the tides quickly. Kurma told the Nine Dragons (his elite disciples) to assist Gale, and they quickly evened out the battle. The Nine Dragons were skillful masters of life force, and so they were able to quickly subdue the minions by utilizing energy beams and empowered melee attacks. By now, the battle was completely in the rebellion’s favor, and it seemed that it would be a decisive victory. Gale swiftly advanced towards the void squire to end the battle. As he raised his sword to deliver the finishing blow, the squire kneeled down, as if he was surrendering. Just as Gale’s sword was about to pierce his armor, the tyrant’s minion suddenly lunged at blinding speeds. In the blink of an eye, the Hurricane Blade went flying out of Gale’s hand into the air… and right into the void squire’s sheath. Appalled, Gale looked at his empty hand, flabbergasted at what just happened. He had severely underestimated the power of the void squire, as the seemingly defeated soldier had performed an advanced flash counter on Gale. Before he even had the chance to react, his opponent’s blade had already pierced through Gale’s chest. He fell down in agony as blood flowed from the open gash. The triumphant squire raised his bloody sword above the defeated hero’s corpse and cackled. Yet, as he was walking away from the battlefield, a powerful gust of wind knocked him down face-first onto the rough terrain. Stunned, the void squire looked behind him and saw Gale floating in the air behind him.
	“What… what!? This cannot be!” Kurma appeared beside the undead warrior and chuckled.
	“Do you really think it is that easy to slay a hero of the rebellion? Or, should I say, the Chosen One of the Wind?” Gale’s eyes turned gray as winds swirled at high speeds around him. He raised his hand to the sky, gathering all of the whirling air around him into one massive, powerful, destructive, terrifying tornado. Kurma infused a large amount of life force into the formidable force of nature, and the Messenger of the Wind sent the tornado straight towards the tyrant’s army. As chaos erupted in the enemy lines, Kurma, Enzo, Kali, Amun, and Aella flew towards the palace on a spirit dragon. They were about to duel the tyrant and his elite forces and end everything once and for all.
	The dragon burst through the tall stained glass windows of the palace and the heroes rolled onto the ground. In front of them, there were three corridors: One led to the left, one led to the right, and one led straight ahead. After a brief discussion, they agreed that Kali and Amun would go to the right, Enzo would go to the left, and Kurma and Aella would go forward.
	“Well, this is going to be fun,” Amun chuckled.
	“Yeah,” replied Kali. “Hopefully we can deal with the enemy as quickly as possible so we can help our friends.” Amun rummaged inside his pocket and pulled out two rainbow potions, which contained strength, speed, and shield.
	“Take one of these beforehand, as there might be traps ahead,” the alchemist said as he handed a potion to Kali.” They drank the brew and continued to walk forward until they came to the center of a massive multi-floor library. The Shadow Rebellion stood on the bottom floor and admired the rich collection of valuable volumes. Abruptly, a tiny rock blasted at high speeds towards Kali’s head. Thankfully, she was able to dodge it due to the effects of the speed potion. Surprised, she looked up and saw a sorceress and a jester standing on the top balcony.
	“Well, well, well. What have we here,” said the sorceress in a soft, deceiving voice. “Isn’t this the famous Shadow Rebellion, the dynamic duo that escaped the hands of death?”
	Smiling, Amun replied with confidence. “Yup, that’s us. I assume you are the sorceress and jester that Gale talked about?”
	“Indeed, that is us!” Answered the jester in a merry tone. “As a jester, of course, I must make a joke. What do you call someone who opposes our glorious king?”
	“Well, I think any person in their right mind would call them a courageous hero fighting for justice.” Amun replied with a smirk.
	“That is quite a witty answer, but no. You should call them… dead.” The jester replied cheerfully.
	“Bro, shut your mouth. You are not slick.” Kali rolled her eyes. “I swear, your terrible jokes are the reason you got demoted to organizing books all day in a library, but you can’t even read the titles through your goofy mask.”
	“Ohhhhhh!” Amun chuckled in delight. “I would not take that if I were you. You just got completely roasted, cooked, and destroyed.”
	“Oh, don’t be so mean to me. I was just about to give you a present!” said the jester. He pulled out two presents from his pocket. He dropped one on the ground beneath him and threw one at the duo. The first present contained potent buffs, while the second one exploded when it contacted the floor. Kali and Amun jumped back while the sorceress started shooting minute meteors rapidly, as if her hands were a machine gun. The Shadow Rebellion dodged and weaved through the bullets as they sprinted towards their enemy. While the sorceress shot at the heroes, the jester continued to bombard them with explosive presents. Amun threw Kali a jump potion, and after they drank it, they leaped up to the top balcony and started a close-range melee battle. The fighters moved at blinding speeds and threw super-charged hits at each other. After a few minutes of intense brawling, the jester and the sorceress retreated, gaining distance from the dynamic duo.
	“Are you scared, lil bro?” mocked Amun. Unbeknownst to him, the enemy was preparing a powerful, explosive rain of fire…
	Enzo walked down the hallway on high alert, unlike the young duo. He knew that he was on his own, and that there were most certainly traps waiting for him. Indeed, the moment he stepped into the palace coliseum, the door slammed behind him, trapping him inside. A knight shrouded in a dark purple cloak entered the arena, standing directly across from Enzo. The rebellion leader shouted, “Who are you, mysterious knight? Have you imprisoned me, or are you also trapped?” The knight did not reply and continued to advance towards Enzo. Sensing an incoming duel, he reluctantly pulled out his Sword of Valor and walked cautiously towards the mysterious figure. The knight’s armor began to emit a purple glow as void energy crackled in the air around him. He pulled out a sharp sword adorned with shattered crystals and started to sprint towards Enzo. The hero took a look at the purple weapon and his eyes widened in horror. The opponent he was about to face was the legendary Knight of the Void, who wielded the ancient Inanus Blade. Enzo gritted his teeth and sent out a few light beams at the knight, but he immediately dodged them, with amazing dexterity and agility. The rebellion leader was forced to engage, and he was instantly shaken by the champion of the void’s strength. He was already at a disadvantageous position, and all he could do was parry while retreating. The knight ruthlessly persisted, dealing heavy blow by blow. He charged void energy into his next strike and performed a wide sweep, knocking Enzo back three feet. The hero quickly got back up, but he saw that his armor was deteriorating because of the knight’s void decay. The leader of the great rebellion blew the Horn of Justice, as he knew that this battle may well be his last stand.
	“Alright, Aella, you’re going to have to be the one who fights the dragon,” Kurma sighed.
	“I think I’m going to be fine,” Aella replied. “I mean, if I’m about to die, you can revive me, right?”
	Kurma chuckled. “Indeed, this is why I accompanied you. However, I heard from Gale that the dragon is being mind controlled, so we cannot kill it. If we are able to successfully rescue it, though, then the void dragons will be saved.”
	The heroes walked down a long corridor until they came to a large gate. They entered and were shocked to see the tyrant sitting on his throne and stroking the head of a void dragon.
	“Greetings, Kurma. You are quite famous in my kingdom as a wise, benevolent teacher and warrior. However, in reality, you are just a despicable, filthy rebel. But because of your popularity with the people, I’ll offer you a great deal, considering your current circumstances. Surrender right now, and I’ll keep you alive in captivity.”
	Kurma coldly replied, “You are even worse than I thought, you cruel, malicious tyrant. Today, I have come to take back my kingdom, and I suggest you surrender considering the current circumstances.”
“Looks like someone will be regretting their life choices shortly. But, who are you?” The tyrant cackled, looking at Aella. “Why are you here with these lowly rebels? Go, go back to your parents, puny girl. You should be learning about my glorious conquests in history right now.”
	Aella’s right eye glowed purple with pure hatred and fury. Her blown-off left hand had been completely replaced with a dragon claw, and her right eye had also been restored with the eye of a void dragon. “You… you… your existence is killing me right now. You are the most evil dictator this world will ever know. You know where my parents are? They were killed by you. You know where my school is? It was destroyed by you. And I would also be a corpse rotting on the streets right now if it wasn’t for Kháos. But here I am, ready to tear you limb from limb.” Aella lunged at the tyrant, but the void dragon flew in front of him and blocked the shot. With rage, Aella summoned the dragon head, but it did absolutely nothing to the impenetrable armor of the void dragons. The tyrant’s pet, getting annoyed, swiped her tail at the dragon girl and knocked Aella 10 feet, shattering her dragon scale armor. Kurma attempted to heal the fallen hero, but the tyrant flourished his hand and teleported himself and Kurma into a corridor. Back in the throne room, Aella finally summoned Kháos from the void and mounted him. “Alright, Kháos, do you think you can hold her in a standstill?” He nodded confidently, and the dragon girl steered him towards the manipulated pet.
	“WHAT!?” Kali screamed. The sorceress was bombarding them with explosive pellets that seemed to never stop coming. Amun threw Kali an invisibility potion, and they drank it to retreat before their shield broke.
	“Look who’s running now,” laughed the jester. “What, lil bro? Are you scared?”
	Behind a half burning bookshelf, Amun gave Kali a gray, swirling potion. He explained, “This is a new potion I’ve been brewing. It makes the opponent temporarily fall asleep when thrown at them, and so you can charge your meteor when they’re paralyzed.”
	“Alright, let’s end this quickly,” said Kali. She began charging a huge meteor as Amun swiftly and silently advanced on the unsuspecting enemy. At the right moment, he leaped up to the top balcony and hurled the potion at the sorceress and the jester. The instant he stunned them, Kali released the comet, completely obliterating her opponents to ashes.
	The moment the sorceress died, the tyrant’s pet started to lose control. She thrashed around and mindlessly rammed in all directions. Amidst the chaos, Kháos pushed his head against the other dragon’s head, creating a stalemate.
	The instant Enzo blew the Horn of Justice, a sound never heard before spread rapidly in a hundred mile radius. When it reached the ears of the rebellion soldiers, they instinctively raised their weapons into their sky and began chanting, ‘Veni, vidi, vici!’ The civilians of the capital also followed suit, and their gestures released beams of light that all flew to Enzo. Right away, the leader of the people felt an unimaginable power coursing through his veins. With glowing yellow eyes, he pulled out the Sword of Valor and sent a humongous beam of light that pierced through the Knight of the Void’s armor, annihilating him.
	The second the knight died, Aella felt a strong presence of uncontained void energy. As the two dragons struggled in their forehead war, she crawled onto the uncontrolled dragon’s head. The Child of the Void raised her hand in the air, collecting all of the energy the Knight of the Void had released. Aella slammed her hand down on the rogue dragon’s neck, creating a dark purple column that instantaneously subdued it.
“Kurma, it’s just me and you!” Yelled the tyrant as he flourished his hand, sending void beams at the monk in all directions. The Warrior of Immortality did not respond as he gracefully weaved through the bullets. Although the tyrant released more projectiles after each volley, Kurma just continued to heal his wounds. Infuriated, the cruel oppressor channeled all of his void energy into one nuke and blasted it at the monk. “Farewell, Kurma!” The dictator cried triumphantly…
	From the ashes, Kurma emerged unharmed, unscathed, and unfazed; a spirit phoenix had shielded him from the explosion. The tyrant’s jaw fell to the floor, and he was left both speechless and powerless. With glowing green eyes, the Master of Life Force conjured a spirit dragon and released it at the demonic ruler, finally ending the war…
	As the moon disappeared beneath the horizon, the heroes stood on a cliff overlooking the capital. Good had finally triumphed over evil, and the kingdom had been retaken. In addition, the king and queen had been rescued from captivity and reinstated onto the throne. Enzo looked down on the ruins of the capital and sighed. “Well, restoration is going to take a long time.” Kurma smiled at his brother and pointed to the rising sun.
	“Like the sunrise, our kingdom will always return better than ever before. Like the sunrise, we will always emerge from the horizon, triumphant. And every time we see the sunrise, we will know that it is a new day full of possibilities and opportunities to set things right.”

THE END
